</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Oceans<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://www-ceob.nos.noaa.gov">NOAA Coastal and Estaurine Oceanography Branch</A>
<DD>From the U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration. Includes tide tables, a tide glossary, and overviews of several coastal ecosystem health projects.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.fws.gov/~cep/cepcode.html">Coastal Ecosystems</A>
<DD>A project of the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.alaska.net/~ospic">Oil Spill Public Information Center</A>
<DD>Scientific, economic and legal information on the March 24, 1989, Exxon Valdez oil spill in Prince William Sound, Alaska. Includes a bibliography of final reports from the damage assessment and restoration project, background on the spill, maps and links to related sites.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://whale.wheelock.edu/">WhaleNet</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.geog.umd.edu/wetlands/Marsh.html">Coastal Marsh Project</A>
<DD>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://kabir.umd.edu/Welcome.html">Multiscale Experimental Ecosystem Research Center</A>
<DD>A joint effort of the University of Maryland and EPA focusing on estuaries and coastal wetlands.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://amb1.ccalmr.ogi.edu/">Center for Coastal and Land-Margin Research</A>

</DL>

