<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Federal Documents</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Federal Regulations<br>and Related Documents</H1>

<br>

<HR width=80%>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.access.gpo.gov/su_docs/aces/aaces004.html">GPO Access</a>
<DD>Links to federal depository libraries with searchable full text of the Federal Register, Congressional Record, congressional bills, public laws and General Accounting Office reports. The sites at <A HREF = "http://thorplus.lib.purdue.edu/gpo/">Purdue</A> and <A HREF = "http://www.lib.utk.edu/gpo/GPOsearch.html">Tennessee</A> are the easiest to use.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://law.house.gov/usc.htm">United States Code</A>
<DD>Complete U.S. federal statutes in searchable form.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://law.house.gov/cfr.htm">Code of Federal Regulations</A>
<DD>Complete U.S. federal regulations in searchable form.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.sec.gov/edgarhp.htm">U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission EDGAR database</A></A>
<DD>A database of disclosure documents filed by publicly traded companies, searchable by company name or ticker symbol. See also this explanation of <A HREF="http://www.sec.gov/edaux/forms.htm">the document numbers.</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/EOP/html/other/OMB.html">Office of Management and Budget</A>
<DD>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="gopher://pula.financenet.gov/11/docs/central/omb">Office of Management and Budget circulars</A>
<DD>Includes full text of OMB circulars and related documents, such as "A Citizen's Guide to the 1996 Federal Budget."
<P>

<DT><A HREF="gopher://www.sbaonline.sba.gov:70/11/ignet">IGNet (Inspectors General network)</A>
<DD>Audits, investigations and other reports from the Inspector General offices in many federal
agencies, including the departments of Energy, Health and Human Services, Interior, and
Justice, and the Nuclear Regulatory Commission.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/oigearth/">EPA Office of the Inspector General semiannual reports</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/docs/OCEPAterms">Terms of Environment</A>
<DD>A glossary with non-technical definitions of terms commonly used in EPA documents.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://atsdr1.atsdr.cdc.gov:8080/glossary.html">Glossary of ATSDR Terms</A>
<DD>Non-technical definitions of terms commonly used in by the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry, part of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://govinfo.kerr.orst.edu">Government Information Sharing Project</A>
<DD>Online access to CD-ROM databases maintained by the Oregon State University Library, including U.S. Census data and Regional Economic Information System data.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.census.gov/">Bureau of the Census</A>
<DD>Includes searchable data from the <A HREF = "http://www.census.gov/cdrom/lookup/CMD=LIST/DB=C90STF3A/LEV=STATE">1990 census STF3A tables</A> and lots of other census materials.
<P>


<DT><A HREF="http://www.gao.gov">General Accounting Office</A>
<DD>Home page of the auditing branch of Congress. Includes summaries of recent reports, testimony and policy guidance, plus links to GPO Access sites for full text of reports.
<P>

<DT>White House Electronic Publications Service
<DD>Automatic mailing of White House documents to your e-mail box. For instructions, send an e-mail message to 
<A  HREF="mailto:Publications@Research.AI.MIT.EDU">Publications@Research.AI.MIT.EDU</A> with the word 
"help" (but without the quote marks) in the "subject" line.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://159.142.1.210/Harvest/brokers/ARNFARs/query.html">Federal Acquisition Regulations</A>
<DD>A searchable database.
<P>

</DL>

<HR width=80%>

<P>

