<HEAD>

<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Water Supply</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Water Supplies<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF = "http://www.waterwiser.org/">
WaterWiser, the Water Efficiency Clearinghouse</A>
<DD>Information on water conservation and water efficiency from 
the American Water Works Association and the U.S. Environmental 
Protection Agency. Includes water recycling and reuse, 
water conservation program planning, public education, 
residential retrofit programs, efficient irrigation, integrated resource planning, 
drought and emergency planning and legislation.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://h2o.usgs.gov/public/wid/indexlist.html">U.S. Geological Survey "Earth Facts"</A>
<DD>Includes fact sheets and studies on water resources and other topics, organized by state, 
plus specific subjects such as Chesapeake Bay.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.uwin.siu.edu">Universities Water Information Network</A>
<DD>Includes a database of USGS abstracts, a calendar of water events, directories of water experts and organizations, and a list of links to other water sites.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.uwin.siu.edu:80//WaterSites/browse.html">Wetlist</A>
<DD>A large collection of water-related links, from the Universities Water Information Network.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.awwa.org/">American Water Works Association</A>
<DD>Home page for the organzation representing public drinking water suppliers.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.waterweb.com/">WaterWeb</A>
<DD>An extensive collection of links regarding water treatment technology.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/WRCA/">Water Resources Center Archives</A>
<DD>A collection of books, other documents, and manuscript collections, housed at the University of 
California, Berkeley. Bibliographies and other guides to the collection are available online, along
with instructions for obtaining copies or loans of the materials.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://asset.arsusda.gov/wmrl/wmrl.html">
USDA Water Management Research Laboratory</A>
<DD>Contains a bibliography by topic on drip irrigation articles
and books, a list of articles by WMRL staff (articles are available 
on request in the old-fashioned paper style), research descriptions 
from the lab's 1993 progress report, and a Frequently Asked Questions
file on drip irrigation.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.wiz.uni-kassel.de/kww/projekte/irrig/irrig_i.html">
The World Wide Web Virtual Library Irrigation Page</A> 
<DD>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.sandelman.ocunix.on.ca:80/dams/Overview.html">The Dam and Reservoir Impact Information Archives</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.mp.usbr.gov/">U.S. Bureau of Reclamation, Mid-Pacific Region</A>
<DD>Includes water conservation information.  
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://twri.tamu.edu/">Texas Water Resources Institute</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.great-lakes.net">Great Lakes Information Network</A>
<P>

<P><DT><A HREF = "http://wwwdwr.water.ca.gov/">California Department of Water Resources</A>
<DD>Daily snow sensor reports from the Sierra Nevada and the Cascades, 
reservoir levels and runoff forecasts for important California watersheds. 
Also includes avalanche forecasts and an overview of the State Water Project.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://hydrolab.arsusda.gov/arswater.html">USDA Agricultural Research Service Water Data Base</A>
<DD>Contains extensive data on precipitation and stream flow, air temperatures, topography and soils.
<P>

</DL>

