<H1>Internet Mailing Lists<br> on the Environment<br>and Journalism</H1>

<HR>
<H3>Listserv? What's a Listserv?</H3>
<p>A listserv is a type of software. But more to the point, it's 
one of several related types of software used to operate Internet 
mailing lists. These lists allow you to participate in e-mail 
discussions of wide-ranging topics, including journalism and the 
environment. </p>
<p>If you follow the instructions and send e-mail to 
any of the addresses below, you'll soon receive a note welcoming 
you to the list and telling you how to post messages and how to 
cancel your subscription -- which can be a good thing to know, 
since some of these lists produce as many as 50 messages per day. 
</p>
<p>There are separate sections below for <A HREF = 
"#environmental">environmental</A> and <A HREF = 
"#journalism">journalism</A> mailing lists. 
On the <A HREF = "env_epal.htm">next page</A> are listings of all
the mailing lists currently operated by the U.S. Environmental Protection
Agency, plus environmentally oriented lists at Envirolink and the Institute 
for Global Communications. And if you can't find 
what you're looking for on these pages, then try this nifty<a HREF  
= "http://www.liszt.com"> search tool</a> 
for all of mailing lists on the Internet. Or you can read the <A 
HREF = "gopher://ecosys.drdr.Virginia.EDU:70/11/communication">archives</a> 
of many of these lists. </p>
<p>Here's <A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/impulse/list.html">a nice page</A> 
with lots of instructions on how to use these mailing
lists, if you need more help than you can find here.</P>
<p><em>Finally, a special note for overly 
literal readers:</em> In the "To join" instructions below, 
substitute your first name for "yourfirstname," your last name 
for "yourlastname," and your E-mail address for "yourE-mailaddress." We know, it's confusing. That's life. </p> <HR> 
<A NAME = "environmental"><H3>Environmental lists</H3></a> 

<DL>
<strong><DT>AESP-net
</strong><DD>Association of Energy Service Professionals
<br>To join, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF = "mailto:majordomo@dnai.com">
majordomo@dnai.com</a></em>
with <em>subscribe AESP-net</em> in the body of your e-mail message
and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

<strong><DT>Aeroso-l
</strong><DD>Health Effects of Particulate Matter (Air Pollution).
<br>To join, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF = "mailto:LISTSERV@nic.surfnet.nl">
listserv@nic.surfnet.nl</a></em>
with <em>subscribe Aeroso-l yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

<strong><DT>Aquifer
</strong><DD>Pollution and Groundwater Discharge.
<br>To join, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF = "mailto:LISTSERV@IBACSATA.BITNET">
listserv@ibacsata.bitnet</a></em>
with <em>subscribe Aquifer yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

<strong><DT>Aqua-L
</strong><DD>Discussions on the science,
technologies and business of aquaculture.
<br>To join, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:LISTSERV@VM.UOGUELPH.CA">
listserv@vm.uoguelph.ca</a></em>
with <em>subscribe Aqua-L yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

<strong><DT>Audubon
</strong><DD>Discussions of the National Audubon Society (U.S.).
<br>To join, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:AutoShare@rip.physics.unk.edu">
AutoShare@rip.physics.unk.edu</a></em>
with <em>subscribe Audubon yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

<strong><DT>Bay-Delta Forum
