<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Energy</H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>
<P>
<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://home.ptd.net/~sjrubin/pubutil.htm">The Public Utility Home Page</A>
<DD>Includes links to federal and state statutes and other legal resources on public utilities, relevant environmental resources, utility companies' home pages and other items.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://infoventures.microserve.com/emf/">EMF-Link</A>
<DD>Information on biological and health   
effects of electric and magnetic fields (EMFs) from common sources such   
as power lines, electrical wiring, appliances, medical equipment,   
communications facilities, cellular phones, and computers. 
<P>

<!-- <DT><A HREF="http://www.ntu.ac.sg/~asreid/asianog.htm">Asian Oil and Gas Internet Resources</A>
<DD>Broader in scope than its name implies, this site includes and extensive set of petroleum-related links, and a searchable business directory of Hong Kong.
<P>
-->
<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/EnergyStar.html">EPA Energy Star Program</A>
<DD>Information on EPA's program to encourage the production and use of energy-saving and pollution-preventing computers and other electronic equipment.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/GreenLights.html">EPA Green Lights Program</A>
<DD>EPA's effort to encourage use of energy-saving lighting.
<P>

<DT><em>Wind Energy Weekly</A></em>
<DD>An electronic publication of the American Wind Energy Association. To subscribe, send your request via e-mail to <A HREF="mailto:tomgray@econet.org">tomgray@econet.org</A>.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.ecn.nl/eii/main.html">Energy Information on Internet database</A>
<DD>A collection of links maintained by the Netherlands Energy Research Foundation.
<P>

</DL>

