<HEAD>

<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Weather</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Current Weather and Forecasts<br></H1>

<font size = +2>M</font>any of the sites listed below have hourly forecasts, satellite photos 
and forecast maps from the National Weather Service. Others have
long-range forecasts and climate information.<br>

<HR>

<P>

<DL><DT><A HREF = "http://www.noaa.gov/nws/nws_intro.html">National Weather Service Home Page</A>
<DD>Includes links to many local weather service offices.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.intellicast.com/">Intellicast</A>
<DD>A commercial site with extensive USA and world weather forecasts and ski conditions.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.atmos.uiuc.edu/">The University of Illinois Weather Machine</A>
<DD>Current weather maps, satellite images, animations, forecasts 
and pointers to good sources for climate data.

<P><DT><A HREF = "http://rs560.cl.msu.edu/weather">Michigan State University</A>
<DD>Weather maps and movies. Excellent selection of data 
for Europe and North Africa in addition to North America.

<P><DT><A HREF = "http://wwwdwr.water.ca.gov/">California Department of Water Resources</A>
<DD>Daily snow sensor reports from the Sierra Nevada and the Cascades, 
reservoir levels and runoff forecasts for important California watersheds. 
Also includes avalanche forecasts and an overview of the State Water Project.

<P><DT><A HREF="http://www.uea.ac.uk/~e870/weather.html">Weather Information</A>
<DD>From the University of East Anglia. Includes links to many European sites.

<P><DT><A HREF = "http://www.met.fu-berlin.de/DataSources/MetIndex.html">World Wide Web Virtual Library: Meteorology</A>

</DL>

<P>

<HR width=80%>

<P>

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>

