<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>International<br>Environmental Information<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<H4>Worldwide:</H4>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://sedac.ciesin.org/pidb/pidb-home.html">CIESIN Policy Instruments Database</A>
<DD>Searchable and browsable full text and summaries of treaties and other international agreements related to global environmental change and sustainable development.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.nbs.gov/nbii/iao/">U.S. National Biological Service's International Affairs Home Page</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.stoller.com/iso.htm">ISO 14000 Information</A>
<DD>A privately maintained page on the series of environmental quality management standards (ISO 14000) sparked by the Rio Earth Summit and the GATT negotiations.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="gopher://gaia.info.usaid.gov:70/11/prot_env/dcs">World Resources Institute: Directory of Country Environmental Studies</A>
<DD>A guide to the content and availability of hundreds of national and regional studies on environmental and natural resources conditions. Includes abstracts, and directions for getting full text.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.imf.org/external/np/sec/decdo/contents.htm">Directory of Economic Commodity and Development Organizations</A>
<DD>Includes program descriptions, senior staff lists and phone numbers for more 100 international organizations, from the Abu Dhabi Fund for Development to the World Trade Organization.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.leje.com/wtn.html">World Timber Network</A>
<P>

</DL>

<H4>Europe:</H4>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.cedar.univie.ac.at">Central European Environmental Data Request Facility</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.efi.joensuu.fi/">European Forest Institute</A>
<DD>A non-governmental research institute based in Finland. Site includes institute publications, a calendar of forestry events worldwide, a database of European forestry resources and data on the global timber trade.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.metla.fi/">The Finnish Forest Research Institute</A>
<DD>An institute operating under the Finnish Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry. Includes a link to the World Wide Web Virutal Library Forestry page, which is maintained by the institute.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://ifs.plants.ox.ac.uk/OFI/tfrg/ofi.htm">Oxford Forestry Institute</A>
<P>

</DL>

<H4>Asia:</H4>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://frim.gov.my/">Forest Research Institute of Malaysia</A>
<P>

<!-- <DT><A HREF="http://www.ntu.ac.sg/~asreid/asianog.htm">Asian Oil and Gas Internet Resources</A>
<DD>Broader in scope than its name implies, this site includes and extensive set of petroleum-related links, and a searchable business directory of Hong Kong.
<P>
-->
</DL>

<H4>Africa:</H4>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.web.apc.org/~econews/">EcoNews Africa</A>
<DD>Full-text access to news bulletins produced by a coalition of non-government groups since September 1994.
<P>

</DL>

