<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Online Environmental Journals<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL>

<DT><EM><A HREF="http://www.apn.com/info/greenwire/">Greenwire</A></EM>
<DD>Carries the daily news and 
commentary from dozens of U.S. and international sources, plus publish newsmaker interviews, 
month-ahead calendars, humor, and special reports on important trends and developments. Free
<A HREF="http://www.apn.com/info/greenwire/sample.htm">sample issue</A> and 
<A HREF="http://www.apn.com/info/greenwire/signup.htm">subscription</A> 
information are available.
<P>

<DT><EM><A HREF="http://ehpnet1.niehs.nih.gov/">Environmental Health Perspectives</A></EM>
<DD>A free monthly scientific journal published online and in print by the National Institute of
Environmental Health Sciences, National Institutes of Health.
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF = "http://www.islandpress.com/Eco-Compass/ECOCOMPHOME.HTM">Ecocompass</em></a><br>
<DD>A free monthly newsletter featuring descriptions
of and pointers to Internet resources of interest to professionals,
academics, and citizen activists concerned with the environment.<br>
<P>

<strong><DT>Enviro-Newsbrief
</strong><Dd>A free daily update providing news of interest to EPA staff. Includes information from current news sources, including newspapers, newsletters, and other publications.
To subscribe, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:listserver@unixmail.rtpnc.epa.gov">
listserver@unixmail.rtpnc.epa.gov</a></em>
with <em>subscribe environb-l yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.
<P>
<DT><em><A HREF = "http://www.envirolink.org/EcoLink/">
The EcoLink Web Journal</A></em><br>
<DD>Published monthly and free, each issue delves into one ecological topic, including real-life stories, photos, scientific information. and links to related net resources.<br>
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF = "http://www.lib.uidaho.edu:70/docs/egj.html">
The Electronic Green Journal</A></em><br>
<DD>A free professional refereed publication devoted to disseminating information 
concerning sources on international environmental topics including:
assessment, conservation, development, disposal, education,
hazards, pollution, resources, technology, and treatment.
Includes both practical and scholarly articles, bibliographies, reviews, 
editorial  comments, and announcements.<br>
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF="http://www.planeta.com">El Planeta Platica</A></em><br>
<DD>Environmental news about Latin America<br>
<P>

<DT><EM><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/earthtimes/">The Earth Times </A></EM>
<DD>An independent nonprofit newspaper on the environment
and sustainable development, published twice a month in New York 
and Geneva, and produced by veteran journalists. 
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.igc.org/greendisk"><em>The GreenDisk Paperless Environmental Journal</em><br></a>
<DD>(Costs $35 per year and up; distributed via electronic mail or snail-mailed floppy diskettes)<br>
P.O. Box 32224<BR>
Washington, DC 20007<BR>
Phone/FAX toll-free 1-888-GRN-DISK<BR>
Internet: <A HREF = "mailto:greendisk@igc.apc.org">
greendisk@igc.apc.org</A><BR>
Free sample copies available for IBM-compatible or MacIntosh computers.
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF = "ftp://ftp.std.com/periodicals/rachel">
Rachel's Environment & Health Weekly</A></em><br>
<DD>Free, from the <A HREF = "mailto:erf@rachel.clark.net">Environmental Research Foundation,</A> Annapolis, MD.
<P>

<DT><A HREF ="gopher://nmnhgoph.si.edu:70/11/.docs/BCN">
The Smithsonian Institution's <em>Biological Conservation Newsletter</A></em>
<DD>Free, from the National Museum of Natural History, Department of Botany.<br>
<P>
<DT><A HREF ="gopher://nmnhgoph.si.edu/11%2F%2Edocs%2Fconslink%5Fnews">
Other free publications from the Smithsonian's Conslink Network:</A><br>
<DD><UL>
<LI><em>USAID Environment & Natural Resources news,</em> 
from the U.S. Agency for International Development
<LI><em>Biodiversity Conservation Strategy UPDATE, </em>
from the World Resources Institute, the World Conservation Union 
and the United Nations Environment Program
<LI><em>CBSG News,</em> from the IUCN Conservation Breeding Specialist Group
<LI><em>Conservation Digest - The Journal of Biopolitics,</em> from The Parsons Group
<LI><em>The IUCN Deer Specialist Group Newsletter</em>
<LI><em>Environment Information Systems in Sub-Saharan Africa,</em>
from the World Bank EIS Program
<LI><em>Heron Conservation Newsletter,</em>
published by the IUCN, BirdLife, and IWRB Heron Specialist Group
<LI><em>Boletin Humedales de Mexico,</em>
published by Humedales paras las Americas Oficina Mexico
<LI><em>Tragopan,</em> published by World Pheasant Association / BirdLife / 
Species Survival Commission Pheasant Specialist Group
<LI><em>Society for Conservation Biology Newsletter</em>
<LI><em>Tropinet,</em> from the Association for Tropical Biology, 
Organization for Tropical Studies, and Smithsonian Institution
<LI><em>DevelopNet News,</em> published by Volunteers in Technical Assistance.<br>
</UL>
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF = "http://cygnus-group.com/ULS/Current_ULS_Reports/Reports.html">
The ULS (Use Less Stuff) Report</A></em><br>
<DD>Free, with articles on waste reduction and packaging, plus links to 
environmental and educational WWW sites.<br>
<P>

<DT><em><A HREF="http://www.voyagepub.com/publish">Voyage: Science and the Environment</A></em>
<DD>A free Internet magazine with summaries of environmental stories. Designed for teachers.
<P>

<DT><EM><A HREF="http://www.iue.it/WGES/Welcome.html">Newsletter of the Working Group on Environmental Studies</A></EM>
<DD>Discussion of worldwide problems from the perspective of law, politics and economics. Free, published by the European University Institute in Florence, Italy.
<P>
<strong><DT>EnviroNews Service 
</strong><DD>Daily updates with news about the environment from around the world. Free. 
To subscribe, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:listproc@envirolink.org">
listproc@envirolink.org</a></em>
with <em>subscribe Environews yourfirstname yourlastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.
<P>
<strong><DT>Internet Newsbrief 
</strong><Dd>A free weekly service from the EPA Headquarters library that provides a sampling of new and/or useful Internet resources for EPA staff and other environmental professionals.  
To subscribe, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:listserver@unixmail.rtpnc.epa.gov">
listserver@unixmail.rtpnc.epa.gov</a></em>
with <em>subscribe internetnb-l firstname lastname</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.
<P>
<strong><DT>[GAO] Daybook
</strong><DD>A free daily electronic posting of new reports and testimony from the U.S. General Accounting Office, Congress' Watchdog agency.
To subscribe, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:majordomo@www.gao.gov">
majordomo@www.gao.gov</a></em>
with <em>subscribe daybook</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.
<P>
<DT><STRONG>Conservation Ecology</STRONG>
<DD>Distribution list for <em>Conservation Ecology,</em> a free online publication of the <A HREF = "http://www.sdsc.edu/1/SDSC/Research/Comp_Bio/ESA/ESA.html">Ecological Society of America.</a> Initial call for papers will be in late summer/early fall 1995 and publication will commence in early 1996. Subscribers will be automatically notified
of these events. To subscribe, send e-mail to:<em><A HREF ="mailto:subscribe@journal.biology.carleton.ca">
subscribe@journal.biology.carleton.ca</a></em> with <em>subscribe conservation-ecology yourE-mailaddress
</em> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the "Subject:" line.

</DL>

