<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Water Pollution<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/OWOW/indic/">Environmental Impacts of Water 
Quality in the United States</A>
<DD>Published by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, describes water 
quality in the United States using a set of 18 environmental indicators 
that measure progress toward national water goals and objectives.
<P>


<DT><A HREF="http://www.nal.usda.gov/wqic/">Water Quality Information Center of the National Agricultural Library</A>
<DD>Includes a bibliographic database of scientific literature.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.heidelberg.edu/WQL/">Heidelberg College Water Quality Laboratory</A>
<DD>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.awwa.org/">American Water Works Association</A>
<DD>Home page for the organzation representing public drinking water suppliers.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.waterweb.com/">WaterWeb</A>
<DD>An extensive collection of links regarding water treatment technology.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/ada/kerrlab.html">EPA Robert S. Kerr Environmental Research Lab</A>
<DD>Home page of an EPA groundwater laboratory, with bibliographic databases on groundwater research, and various groundwater models and manuals.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.great-lakes.net">Great Lakes Information Network</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://gwrp.cciw.ca/aerb.html">Canadian National Water Research Institute, Aquatic Ecosystem Restoration Branch</A>
<P>

</DL>

