<HEAD>

<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Pesticides</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Pesticides<br></H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL><DT><A HREF = "http://ace.orst.edu/info/extoxnet/">
Extension Toxicology Network, Oregon State University</A>
<DD>Excellent site for toxicology data; includes pesticide information
profiles, toxicology information briefs and issues of concern; fact sheets;
news about toxicology issues; newsletters and resources for toxicology
information. Searchable.<br>
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "gopher://gopher.nih.gov/11/clin/cancernet/facts/risk">
National Cancer Institute: CancerNet</A>
<DD>Fact sheets on risk factors and possible causes of cancer. Includes
authoritative discussions of electromagnetic radiation; pesticides; second-hand
smoke; asbestos; fluoridated water; Agent Orange and cellular phones.<br>
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://atsdr1.atsdr.cdc.gov:8080/atsdrhome.html">
Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry</A>
<DD>From the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. Includes HazDat 
(a database of contaminants found at Superfund sites, searchable by geographical 
area). Also, toxicological profiles of hazardous substances, public health
statements concerning hazardous substances, the "Hazardous Substances & Public 
Health" newsletter, and "ToxFAQs:" Frequently Asked Questions about chemicals and 
pesticides.<br>
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "gopher://gopher.nctr.fda.gov/">
National Center for Toxicological Research</A>
<DD>From the U.S. Food & Drug Administration. Includes a bibliography on
environmental estrogens.<br>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/DataSubmittersList/">Pesticide Data Submitters List</A>
<DD>Online access to names of companies and others that have provided data to the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency on the health and environmental effects of pesticides. Includes an explanation of how to use the data.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://h2o.usgs.gov/public/pubs/bat/bat000.html">U.S. Geological Survey: Agricultural Land and Chemical Use database</A>
<DD>Includes a 1994 report and accompanying database (with mapping software layers) on agricultural practices, herbicide and fertilizer use, and land use in the lower 48 states. Data is broken down to the county level.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/docs/OPPTS_Harmonized/">EPA Office of Prevention, Pesticides and Toxic Substances</A>
<DD>Test guidelines.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.panna.org/panna/">Pesticide Action Network of North America</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.aphis.usda.gov/nbci/nbci.html">National Biological Control Institute</A>
<DD>From the U.S. Department of Agriculture. Includes publications and technical information on biological pest control, and copies of the institute's newsletter.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://ipm_www.ncsu.edu/cernag/cern.html">
The World Wide Web Virtual Library Agriculture Page</A>
<DD>Links to hundreds of agricultural WWW sites around the world.<br>
<P>

<!-- <DT><A HREF = "http://salem10nt.odf.state.or.us/homepage.html">
Oregon Department of Forestry</A>
<DD>Forest practices, state lands, fire protection, insects and disease,
urban forestry, news.<br>
<P>
-->

</DL>

<STRONG>Entomology (fancy word for "bugs")</STRONG>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.colostate.edu/Depts/Entomology/ent.html">Colorado State University Entomology WWW Site</A>
<DD>A large collection of links to bug stuff, including graphics,
images, bug movies (mpeg viewer required) publications on pests, 
pest management and pesticides, insect-oriented listservers and 
newsgroups, and more.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://bluehen.ags.udel.edu/insects/descriptions/entohome.html">On-line Insect Database</A>
<DD>From the University of Delaware College of 
Agricultural Sciences. Includes bug images and descriptions. 
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.msstate.edu/Entomology/EntHome.html">The Resistant Pest Management Newsletter</A>
<DD>From Mississippi State University. 
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.public.iastate.edu/~entomology/">Iowa State University Entomology Web Site</A>
<DD>Still more bug stuff.
<P>

</DL>


