<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Chemicals</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Chemicals</H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR width=80%>
<P>
<H3>Databases:</H3>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/enviro/html/ef_home.html">ENVIROFACTS</A>
<DD>Online access to five major EPA databases, including the Toxic Release Inventory, and databases associated with Superfund, the Clean Water Act and the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.econet.apc.org/hotspots/bhopal/rtknet.html">Toxic Release Inventory data</A>
<DD>Online access to EPA's database of industrial chemical emissions. Also see <A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/TRI_Cover93/">TRI ARC/INFO Coverages</A> for an EPA collection of TRI data mapped in the ARC/INFO format, which can be read by most desktop mapping software programs.
<P>
</DL>
<H3>Toxicology information:</H3>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF = "http://ace.ace.orst.edu/info/extoxnet/">
Extension Toxicology Network, Oregon State University</A>
<DD>Excellent site for toxicology data; includes pesticide information
profiles, toxicology information briefs and issues of concern; fact sheets;
news about toxicology issues; newsletters and resources for toxicology
information. Includes contributions from the University of California-Davis, 
Oregon State University, Michigan State University, and Cornell University.
Searchable.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.ciit.org">
Chemical Industry Institute of Toxicology</A>
<DD>Includes CIIT Impact (single-page summaries of CIIT toxicological
research with references to published literature).
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "gopher://gopher.nih.gov/11/clin/cancernet/facts/risk">
National Cancer Institute: CancerNet</A>
<DD>Fact sheets on risk factors and possible causes of cancer. Includes
authoritative discussions of electromagnetic radiation; pesticides; second-hand
smoke; asbestos; fluoridated water; Agent Orange and cellular phones.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://atsdr1.atsdr.cdc.gov:8080/atsdrhome.html">
Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry</A>
<DD>From the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. Includes HazDat 
(a database of contaminants found at Superfund sites, searchable by geographical 
area). Also, toxicological profiles of hazardous substances, public health
statements concerning hazardous substances, the "Hazardous Substances & Public 
Health" newsletter, and "ToxFAQs:" Frequently Asked Questions about chemicals and 
pesticides.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://ntp-server.niehs.nih.gov/">
National Toxicology Program</A>
<DD>Abstracts of published toxicological data; information about chemicals and 
technological processes that are known or reasonably suspected to be 
carcinogenic.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "http://www.chem.ucla.edu/chempointers.html">
The World Wide Web Virtual Library: Chemistry</A>
<DD>at UCLA
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/docs/OPPTS_Harmonized/">EPA Office of Prevention, Pesticides and Toxic Substances</A>
<DD>Guidelines for toxicity testing.
<P>

<DT><A HREF = "gopher://gopher.nctr.fda.gov/">
National Center for Toxicological Research</A>
<DD>From the U.S. Food & Drug Administration. Includes a bibliography on
environmental estrogens.
<P>

</DL>

<HR width=80%>

<P>

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>

