<HEAD>

<TITLE>EnvJourn Home Page: Forests</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><strong><em><A HREF = "env_home.htm">SEJ page top</A> | 
<A HREF = "env_srch.htm">Search this site</A> | 
<A HREF = "net_srch.htm">Search the Internet</A> | 
<A HREF = "mailto:clemings@cris.com">Comments</A></em></strong><br>
</CENTER>

<br>

<IMG ALT = "Society of Environmental Journalists logo" width=68 height=104 ALIGN = LEFT HSPACE  = 10 SRC  = "sej_half.gif">

<H1>Forests and Forestry</H1>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<HR>

<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.fs.fed.us/">Forest Service, U.S. Department of Agriculture</A>
<DD>

<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.afseee.org/">Association of Forest Service Employees for Environmental Ethics</A>
<DD>Home page for a group of dissident Forest Service employees and their supporters.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.pacificrim.net/~nwea/">Northwest Ecosystem Alliance</A>
<DD>An environmental group based in Bellingham, Wash., amd focusing on forestry and salmon issues in the Pacific Northwest.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://mf.ncr.forestry.ca/sof/sof.html">The State of Canada's Forests, 1994 (Summary)</A>
<DD>Includes the introduction, a table of contents, and instructions for ordering the entire free report.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.ran.org/ran">Rainforest Action Network</A>
<DD>Home page of an environmental group . Includes copies of the World Rainforest Report, information about EcoTourism, and a directory of world rainforest movement contacts by region.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/forestry/unasylva/">Unasylva: A Quarterly Journal of Forests and Forest Industries</A>
<DD>Published by the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://frim.gov.my/">Forest Research Institute of Malaysia</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.efi.joensuu.fi/">European Forest Institute</A>
<DD>A non-governmental research institute based in Finland. Site includes institute publications, a calendar of forestry events worldwide, a database of European forestry resources and data on the global timber trade.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.metla.fi/">The Finnish Forest Research Institute</A>
<DD>An institute operating under the Finnish Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry. Includes a link to the World Wide Web Virutal Library Forestry page, which is maintained by the institute.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://ifs.plants.ox.ac.uk/OFI/tfrg/ofi.htm">Oxford Forestry Institute</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.mbnet.mb.ca/linkages/forestry/forest.html">Global Forest Policy</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.leje.com/wtn.html">World Timber Network</A>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:70/11/environment/forests">EcoNet Forest Gopher</A>
<DD>Includes information about forestry advocacy groups and links to their sites.
<P>

</DL>

<HR width=80%>

<P>

