<p><strong><u>Federal and Provincial Agencies</u></strong> <br>
<br>
<strong>Canada Post </strong><br>
Maple Ridge's main post office is located at 11841-224th Street. Other postal outlets 
offering services on a smaller scale can be found throughout Maple Ridge. <br>
<br>
<strong>Employment and Immigration Office </strong><br>
The Canada Employment Centre is located at 22335 Lougheed Highway. <br>
<br>
<strong>Government Agent Office / Motor Vehicle Branch </strong><br>
Located at 22787 Dewdney Trunk Road, these offices have merged to offer their services 
at greater convenience to their clients. <br>
<br>
<strong>B.C. Assessment Authority</strong><br>
The B.C. Assessment Authority's task is to assess land values for taxation purposes. The 
office has recently moved to the nearby Municipality of Pitt Meadows at 19141 Ford 
Road, where it serves communities from the TriCities (Coquitlam, Port Coquitlam, and Port 
Moody), to the Northeast Fraser Valley. <br>
<br>
<strong>Insurance Corporation of British Columbia (ICBC)</strong> <br>
The claims centre is located at 22811 Dewdney Trunk Road. You may also use a 
Dial-A-Claim phone line to file an accident claim with ICBC. <br>
<br>
<strong>Ministry of Social Services </strong><br>
District offices are: Maple Ridge East - #102-22522 Lougheed Highway, Maple Ridge 
West - 12240 Harris Road, Pitt Meadows. <br>
<br>
<strong>Attorney General </strong><br>
Services available within the District include: Probation Office, Provincial Court, Family 
Court, Small Claims Court, and Crown Counsel Office. <br>
<br>
<strong>Environmental Services</strong> <br>
A Conservation Officer for the District is located in the District Field Office at 20450 
Dewdney Trunk Road. </p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
