<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Leisure Facilities</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Leisure Facilities</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font></td><td align=right><img src="bouncebball.gif" align=bottom width=42 height=80> <img src="smalllogo.gif" align=bottom width=106 height=61></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left><font size=3><b>Community Facilities - Public<br>
</b>The District of Maple Ridge boasts a wide variety of leisure facilities, both public and 
private. Choose among options as varied as our award-winning Leisure Centre and our half 
dozen golf courses. Get yourself into some fun!<br>
</font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><font size=3><b>Leisure Centre<br>
</b>This award-winning centre has three indoor swimming pools for toddlers, 
recreational swimming, and lessons; a large swirl pool, two saunas, fitness 
equipment, and change rooms equipped with lockers; a poolside restaurant, 
lounge, and youth centre. The many programs offered at the centre include 
swimming lessons, aqua-fit classes, and hydro-fit for seniors. The fitness 
program offers fitness testing, counselling, training, aerobics, and weights. 
Up-to-date equipment, including shower wheelchairs and pool lifts, makes 
Ridge Meadows aquatic programs accessible to people of all abilities. Call 
467-7322 for more information.</font></td><td><img src="boy_basketball.gif" align=bottom width=83 height=250></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3><b>Recreation Complex</b><em><b><br>
</b></em>Facilities in the complex include an ice arena and the Old Library Auditorium; formerly 
Maple Ridge's Library, it is now the site of many community events. The arena is used from 
August to March as an ice rink, and from April to July as a dry floor facility for large special 
events.<br>
<br>
<b>Curling Rink</b></font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>The Curling Rink is home to the Golden Ears Curling Club for the months of September to 
April. This Club offers a wide range of recreational and competitive curling opportunities. 
Anyone interested in becoming involved can call the Club at 463-4813.<br>
In the months of May through August this facility is used for special events and it is home to 
the Youth Services &quot;Neutral Zone.&quot;<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Martial Arts Centre / Craft Studio Complex<br>
</b>This facility houses a martial arts centre, boxing centre, craft studio, pottery studio, 
darkrooms, and the Maple Ridge Art Gallery.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Centennial Centre<br>
</b>The Centre contains a senior adult lounge, billiard room, kitchen, and a large banquet room 
that can be divided into several small rooms. It is located within Memorial Peace Park, and 
is home to the Elderly Citizens' Recreation Association (ECRA) and the many activities and 
programs available for adults 55 plus. For more information on facility rental call 467-7348. 
For more information on ECRA please call 467-4993.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Hammond Community Centre and Pool</b></font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>Hammond Community Centre is the focal point of the Hammond neighbourhood. Facilities 
include an outdoor pool (open during the summer months), playground area, sports fields, 
and a banquet hall, kitchen, and meeting room. For information on the programs and 
facilities call the Hammond Community Association at 465-8515.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Sports Fields<br>
</b>Maple Ridge's many sports fields host teams of children's and adults' soccer and baseball 
throughout the school year. Rain or shine, the game must go on! For information on 
community sports fields, call Parks &amp; Leisure Services at 467-7438.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Private Facilities<br>
</b>In addition to Maple Ridge's public facilities, many private organizations offer recreation 
opportunities. Golf is a favourite pastime of West Coasters, and Maple Ridge's six scenic 
courses offer year-round enjoyment. Riding clubs and Equestrian centres also flourish in 
this, the &quot;Horse Capital of Canada.&quot; Many fitness centres, gymnastics clubs, dance studios, 
and martial arts organizations help to keep Maple Ridge a very active community.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Community Halls<br>
</b>Including Hammond Community Centre and the Old Library Auditorium, Maple Ridge has 
13 community halls, which host gatherings as diverse as preschool classes and wedding 
receptions. For facility rental information, call Parks &amp; Leisure Services at 467-7438.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><strong>Maple Ridge Lawn Bowling</strong></font><font size=4><br>
</font><font size=3>The Maple Ridge Lawn Bowling Facility is the first Henselite Tru-Draw outdoor lawn 
bowling facility in B.C. The 1996 Season will be April 1 to October 31. Greens are open 
for morning, afternoon, and evening bowling, seven days week. For membership 
application or information call Ron Tregidgo 463-5234.</font> </p>
<p><font size=3><b>Yennadon Community Association<br>
</b>The Yennadon Community Centre is renovated and ready for use by the community. Parks 
&amp; Leisure Services will be working with the area residents to assist with the development of 
a Neighbourhood Steering Association which will oversee the direction of programs and 
services at the Centre. Facility rentals are available, contact Sue Wheeler 467-7308.<b><br>
<br>
Whonnock Community Association<br>
</b>Whonnock Community Association invites residents of the east side of Maple Ridge to 
enjoy a variety of leisure activities, implemented in partnership with many community 
organizations. Facility rentals are available, contact Allan Springman 462-8212.</font><font size=4><b><br>
<br>
</b></font><font size=3><b>Places of Worship</b> <br>
Different denominations currently active in the Maple Ridge community include Anglican, 
Baptist, United, and Catholic, as well as many others.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>

