             Vacation, Holiday, Fraser Valley, Maple Ridge, Government,
             Lower Mainland, Mountains, Alouette, Golden Ears, Park, 
             Parks">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Maps</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge<br>
<br>
</u></font><font size=3>Planning a visit or move to Maple Ridge? Or maybe you 
just need to know where a certain road is. Be sure to 
check out the maps we have below.</font></td><td align=right valign=top><img src="map_main.gif" align=bottom width=199 height=133></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left><font size=3><strong>Maple Ridge Street Map<br>
</strong></font>Here is a complete street map of Maple Ridge. The map uses new technology on the web 
to give you a map that is full screen, has a built-in magnifying function, pans, and shows 
every street and river in Maple Ridge. </p>
<p align=left>This map requires Netscape 2.0 or later or MS Explorer 3.0 and a plugin from<br>
<img src="bulletweb.gif" align=top width=17 height=17> <a href="http://www.futurewave.com">FutureWave</a>. (www.futurewave.com) </p>
<p align=left>Once you have the plugin installed...you have a couple of options. There is one large street 
map (<em>over 100 K, recommended for direct connections</em>) and another that is divided into 
East and West regions that are ideal for dial up connections. The choices are below. </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table width=550>
<tr><td align=center valign=top width=25%><a href="mrmapwest.html"><img src="mapiconwest.gif" alt="West Map icon" align=bottom border=0 width=89 height=114></a><br>
Maple Ridge<br>
<img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> <a href="mrmapwest.html">West of 240th</a><br>
(74k)<br>
