<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Committees</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Advisory Committees</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
</td><td align=center valign=top><br>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p><b>Social Planning Advisory Committee</b> </p>
<p>The Social Planning Advisory Committee (SPAC) advises Municipal Council on matters 
relating to social planning and the social needs, social well-being, and social development of 
the community. Past and current projects include a child and youth project, an affordable 
housing study, an information and referral service project, a neighbourhood development 
study, and participation in the OCP Review. <br>
<br>
The Committee includes five community representatives, nine representatives from 
government and community agencies, and one Municipal Councillor. SPAC has a telephone 
hotline at 467&#173;7383 if you have any questions or comments about social planning in our 
community. <br>
<br>
<b>Heritage Advisory Committee<br>
<br>
</b>The Heritage Advisory Committee (HAC) advises Municipal Council on matters relating to 
heritage conservation. Past and current projects include the Heritage Plaque program, 
<font size=4><strong><img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16></strong></font><a href="heritage_awards.html"><strong>Heritage Awards</strong></a>, Heritage &quot;Walkabouts,&quot; restoration of the Wharfingers Office at Port 
Haney Wharf in conjunction with the Historical Society, preparation of the Heritage 
Strategy and participation in the OCP Review. Future projects include a Heritage Inventory 
and Heritage Management Plan. <br>
<br>
The Committee is appointed by Council and representatives include Councillor Candace 
Gordon as Council Liaison, Committee Chair Bernice Gehring and Shelia Nickols from the 
Maple Ridge Historical Society, and Community-at-Large members Eric Phillips, Gerry 
Fairweather, and Joseph Robinsmith.<br>
<br>
<i>For information on either of the above, contact Sharon Folkes at 463-5221 Ext. 281 
or e-mail </i><img src="email_leaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> <a href="mailto:sharon_folkes@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca">sharon_folkes@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca</a><i><br>
</i></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>


