<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Demographics</title>
<meta name="description" content="Maple Ridge, British Columbia,
             Your source for information on Maple Ridge!  Check out what Maple Ridge has to offer!">
<meta name="keywords" content="Maple Ridge, District of Maple Ridge,
             Pitt Meadows, Haney, British Columbia, Tourism, Business,
             Vacation, Holiday, Fraser Valley, Maple Ridge, Government,
             Lower Mainland, Mountains, Alouette, Golden Ears, Park, 
             Parks">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Demographics</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font></td><td align=right valign=top><img src="demographics_main.gif" align=bottom width=108 height=93></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3>In July of 1995, the District of Maple Ridge became a member of the Greater Vancouver 
Regional District (GVRD). Comprising Lower Mainland communities from Vancouver east 
as far as Maple Ridge, and from North Vancouver down to White Rock, the GVRD is 
located at the southwest corner of the British Columbia mainland and is home to one half of 
the province's population.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Over the past decade Maple Ridge has been one of the fastest growing municipalities within 
the GVRD. Growth rates for the Greater Vancouver Regional District have averaged 2.7% 
annually, with growth rates for Maple Ridge averaging nearly 5% over the last ten years. 
The rate of population growth for Maple Ridge has been slower in the 1990's than during 
the boom years of the late 1980's. Average rates have declined from over 6% during the 
five years from 1986-1991, to less than 4% during 1991-1996. The current annual rate of 
growth is estimated at 3%.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Maple Ridge's 1996 population is estimated to be 58,088. This figure is based on 
projections from our 1991 census figures. Given an average growth rate that is slightly 
higher than the overall growth in GVRD communities, we anticipate an annual population 
growth rate of 3% over the next five years.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>The graph below illustrates population projections on the basis of growth rates of 1%, 3%, 
and 5%. By the year 2021, our population will reach 72,331 at a 1% growth rate; 122,815 
at a 3% rate; and 206,000 at a rate of 5%.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Population Projections for Maple Ridge, from 1991 to 2021</b></font><font size=2><b><br>
</b></font></p>
<p align=center><font size=5><b><img src="population_chart.jpg" align=bottom width=290 height=175><br>
</b></font><font size=3><tt>Persons (000's)</tt></font><font size=5><b><br>
</b></font></p>
<p align=center><font size=3><b>Population by Age Groups<br>
</b></font><font size=2>1991 (Census)</font> </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1>
<tr><td width=120><font size=2>Total </font></td><td width=120><font size=2>48,420</font> </td></tr>
