<p><font size=3><b>Employment in Maple Ridge / Pitt Meadows Area &amp; Region<br>
</b>Of our labour force, 35.1 percent are employed in the Maple Ridge/Pitt Meadows area. The remainder of the work 
force commutes to employment centres outside of the Maple Ridge/Pitt Meadows area. Maple Ridge residents are 
employed throughout the region as illustrated in Diagram A.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p align=center><font size=3><b>Diagram A: Percentage of Maple Ridge residents employed in Lower Mainland communities.<br>
</b></font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table width=100%>
<tr><td align=right width=50%><img src="employed_labour.gif" align=bottom width=200 height=200></td><td width=50%><img src="employed_labour_mrpm.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 35.1% Maple Ridge / Pitt Meadows<br>
<img src="employed_labour_nes.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 17.3% North East Sector<br>
<img src="employed_labour_other.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 13.6% Other<br>
<img src="employed_labour_bnw.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 13.1% Burnaby / New West<br>
<img src="employed_labour_van.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 11.2% Vancouver<br>
<img src="employed_labour_swl.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 05.1% Surrey / White Rock / Langley<br>
<img src="employed_labour_rich.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> 02.0% Richmond<br>
<img src="employed_labour_ns.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> &gt;1.0% North Shore<br>
<img src="employed_labour_del.jpg" align=bottom width=16 height=16> &gt;1.0% Delta</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3><b>Employment Opportunities in Maple Ridge<br>
</b>As Table 3 illustrates, compared to overall GVRD employment Maple Ridge has a higher than average percentage of 
jobs in the primary, manufacturing, construction, non-commercial services, and government service sectors. Maple 
Ridge has a lower than average percentage in the transportation storage and utilities, wholesale trade, finance, 
insurance and real estate, and commercial services sectors. Retail, non-commercial services and commercial services 
are the dominant sources of employment in Maple Ridge. <br>
<br>
</font></p>
<p align=center><font size=3><b>Table 3 Distribution of Employment in Maple Ridge - 1994 </b></font></p>
