<tr><td width=258><font size=2>Total</font></td><td width=71><font size=2>16,541</font> </td><td width=71><font size=2>100.0%</font> </td><td width=71><font size=2>100.0%</font> </td><td width=71><font size=2>1,390</font></td><td width=71><font size=2>100.0%</font></td><td width=71><font size=2>100.0%</font></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><font size=2>* Finance, Insurance, Real Estate<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3>There are approximately 1,747 licensed businesses in Maple Ridge, 37 percent of which are home-based businesses. 
Home businesses increased from 350 in 1993 to approximately 700 in 1995; they now total 8 percent of our local 
jobs.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Future Employment in Maple Ridge<br>
</b>Future employment projections for Maple Ridge depend a great deal upon population growth, affordable housing, and 
services. Based on the 1991 population census figures at a 1%, 3%, and 5% population growth rate, the future 
employment projections are as follows:</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Low Population Growth: at an average 1% per annum population growth, employment will increase at 0.67% per 
annum. Over the period 1995 to 2021, employment would increase by 2,729 jobs or 18% over 1995 levels.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Moderate Population Growth: at an average 3% per annum population growth, employment will increase at 2% per 
annum. Over the period 1995 to 2021, employment would increase by 10,273 jobs or 64% over 1995 levels.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>High Population Growth: at an average 5% per annum population growth, employment will increase at 3.3% per 
annum. Over the period 1995 to 2021, employment would increase by 21,385 or 125% over current levels.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>In any one of these scenarios, Maple Ridge will continue to grow and develop because of our quality of life, medical, 
social, educational, recreational and community services, outdoor recreation activities, and affordable housing. These 
advantages will ensure the continued development of our community.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

