<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Municipal Services</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge<br>
<br>
</u></font><font size=3>This section contains information on Business Licences, Streets and Roads, 
Water, Recycling, and Financial Institutions.</font></td><td align=right valign=top><img src="municipalserv_main.gif" align=bottom width=60 height=100></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3><b>Business Licences<br>
</b>Any owner or operator of a business in Maple Ridge must hold a valid business licence 
obtained from the Municipal Community and Business Relations Department. Submitted 
applications will go through a process for approval, including inspections to determine if all 
building, fire, health, and zoning regulations are complied with. Licence fees may vary 
depending on the type of business or service.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Streets and Roads<br>
</b>The total Municipal road length is 363.5 km, secondary highways total 28.8 km, and 
highways total 22.8 km. The Municipal Operations Centre is responsible for the 
maintenance of Municipal roadways.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Water</b></font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>Maple Ridge maintains its own water system (approximately 294.9 km of mains) and 
purchases water from the Greater Vancouver Regional District. </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2><b>Fixed Annual Water Rates</b></font> </td><td width=295></td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>Residential </font></td><td width=295><font size=2>$94.00 (per dwelling unit)</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>Motels </font></td><td width=295><font size=2>$94.00 (per unit of accommodation)</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>Restaurants </font></td><td width=295><font size=2>$94.00 ( 0-10 chairs, each add'l. chair $9.00)</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>Medical Buildings </font></td><td width=295><font size=2>$94.00 (per doctor/dentist)</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>Boarding House </font></td><td width=295><font size=2>$94.00 (per house; per boarder additional $19.00)</font> </td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><font size=2>In some commercial (e.g. laundromats and service stations) and most industrial establishments,<br>
water consumption is metered and a rate of charge is applied according to consumption.</font> </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2><b>Metered Water Rates</b></font> </td><td width=120></td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2><b>Consumption (m</b></font><sup><font size=2><b>3</b></font></sup><font size=2><b>/Quarter)</b></font> </td><td width=120><font size=2><b>Rate ($/m</b></font><sup><font size=2><b>3)</b></font></sup> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>0-100 </font></td><td width=120><font size=2>.235</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>next 100 used </font></td><td width=120><font size=2>.337</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>next 100 used</font></td><td width=120><font size=2>.284</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>next 200 used </font></td><td width=120><font size=2>.231</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=192><font size=2>next 500 used </font></td><td width=120><font size=2>.155</font> </td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><font size=2>User is charged for a minimum of 100m</font><sup><font size=2>3</font></sup><font size=2> per quarter.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Recycling</b></font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>The Ridge Meadows Recycling Society (RMRS) operates a recycling depot at 
10092-236th Street, close to the Albion Ferry. A blue-box curbside pick-up program 
operates for residential recycling of glass, cardboard, aluminum, tin, and newspaper. 
Businesses are encouraged to recycle through the Commercial Recycling Concept program, 
which includes a flexible pick-up schedule and workshops on how to make your business a 
&quot;Green Office.&quot;</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Financial Institutions</b></font><font size=4><br>
</font><font size=3>There are a variety of financial institutions located in Maple Ridge, with a competitive 
market to ensure a complete range of customer services. The banks and credit unions are 
located throughout the area as a convenience to the customers.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2><b>Name </b></font></td><td width=119><font size=2><b>No. of Branches</b></font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Bank of British Columbia *</font> </td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Bank of Montreal </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>2</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Bank of Nova Scotia </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Canada Trust </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Maple Ridge Community Credit Union **</font> </td><td width=119><font size=2>2</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Royal Bank of Canada</font></td><td width=119><font size=2>2</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>Toronto Dominion </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font> </td></tr>
<tr><td width=288><font size=2>VanCity Credit Union </font></td><td width=119><font size=2>1</font></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><font size=3>*Bank of B.C. is a division of the Hong Kong Bank of Canada.</font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>**Another M.R. Credit Union is proposed for the town core area.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>

