<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - School District #42</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>School District #42</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge<br>
<br>
</u></font><font size=3><img src="bulletweb.gif" align=top width=17 height=17> </font><a href="http://www.schdist42.bc.ca/"><font size=3>School District #42 Web Site</font></a></td><td><img src="schooldist_main.gif" align=bottom width=140 height=80></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left><font size=3>As one of the fastest growing school districts in British Columbia, School District #42 
serves over 12,500 students in the communities of Maple Ridge and Pitt Meadows, with 25 
elementary schools and five secondary schools. The total operating budget for 1994-95 
(excluding debt services) is $68,148,906.<br>
<br>
<b>Keys to Success: Our Philosophy<br>
</b>The &quot;Keys to Success&quot; philosophy was developed in 1992 through a process that involved 
over 200 students, parents, trustees, teachers, administrators, and members of the Maple 
Ridge and Pitt Meadows business communities. The &quot;Keys to Success&quot; statement identifies 
the skills, attitudes, and abilities that secondary school graduates will require to meet the 
challenges of the next century.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Keys to Success&quot; philosophy statement affirms that in School District No. #42 our 
resources and efforts are focused on enabling students to develop seven keys to success.<br>
<em><b><br>
Zest for Learning<br>
</b></em>Enjoys learning and responds to the world as a self-motivated, innovative individual.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Broad Foundation of Knowledge and Skills<br>
</b></em>Acquires, uses, evaluates, and shares academic, fine arts, life, and career preparation skills.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Feelings of Self-Worth<br>
</b></em>Establishes self-confidence and esteem through a positive and realistic outlook.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Interpersonal Relationship</b></em><b>s<br>
</b>Works cooperatively and effectively with others and shows respect for all cultures.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Problem-Solving Abilities<br>
</b></em>Perseveres with purposeful challenges using imaginative, versatile approaches to problems.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Balancing Work and Leisure<br>
</b></em>Maintains physical well-being and emotional contentment through leisure activities and the 
appropriate use of humour.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3><em><b>Global Awareness<br>
</b></em>Protects the environment through appreciation and conservation of the natural world.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Special Programs and Services<br>
</b>In addition to the regular core curriculum offered in all schools, School District #42 offers a 
number of special programs and services, some of which are described below.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Special Needs Support Services<br>
</b>School District #42 is committed to the full service neighbourhood school model. This 
means that students with special challenges are educated in their neighbourhood school with 
their age-appropriate classmates. All students are valued as contributing members of the 
school community.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>At each school, a team of professionals works together to set goals and develop individual 
education plans for children with special challenges. At the District level, specialists such as 
school psychologists, district resource teachers, counsellors, speech and language 
pathologists, and teachers of the hearing or visually impaired are available to provide 
assistance to students, parents, and teachers.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Language Programs<br>
</b>School District #42 offers a variety of languages at both the elementary and secondary 
levels. The District believes that multilingualism is a desirable goal and that students who 
learn a second language will be better able to accept the multifaceted nature of Canadian 
society. Proficiency in a second language can also open doors to employment.<br>
</font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>French Immersion instruction is offered to students at seven schools in the District. 
Students enrolled in the French immersion program are taught the regular British 
Columbia school curriculum, but they receive their instruction in French instead of 
English. The District offers both Early Immersion, beginning in kindergarten, and Late 
Immersion, which starts in grade six.</font><font size=4> </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Japanese, Spanish, and German are offered by certain schools in the District at 
various levels of instruction.</font><font size=4> </font></li>
<li><font size=3>English as a Second Language (ESL) instruction is available for children whose 
mother tongue is not English and who require assistance to reach fluency. At present, 
more than 170 children representing over twenty-five different nationalities are 
receiving ESL instruction, further enriching the community of languages in School 
District #42.</font><font size=4> </font></li>
</ul>
<p><font size=3><b>Career Education<br>
</b>Beginning in the primary grades and continuing on to graduation, students move through 
several stages of career education including career awareness, career exploration, and 
career preparation. Students who are 15 years and older have the opportunity to try a 
variety of work environments through the work experience program. Over 800 businesses, 
industries, and services have participated in this program. Specific training is offered to 
prepare senior secondary students for direct entry into business / industry, and special 
programs prepare some students for advanced placement at post-secondary institutions. 
Over 20 different career preparation programs are offered in the areas of business, 
communications, the performing arts, the service industry, trades, and technical fields.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Community Education<br>
</b>In association with both Ridge Meadows Parks and Leisure Services and the Arts Council, 
School District #42 sponsors a variety of educational and recreational programs to help 
community members fulfill their educational needs. Some of the services offered include:<br>
</font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>Secondary School Completion and Academic Upgrading Programs</font><font size=4> </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Certificate Programs offered through the Business &amp; Office Training Centre</font><font size=4> </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Work Orientation Workshop Program</font><font size=4> </font></li>
<li><font size=3>General Interest, Career / Vocational, and Community Education Courses</font><font size=4> </font></li>
</ul>
<p><font size=3>Classes are offered in a variety of locations throughout Maple Ridge and Pitt Meadows. A 
community education and recreation brochure is published three times a year, listing course 
descriptions, fees, and locations.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3><b>Thomas Haney Centre<br>
</b>Representing a first in Canadian education, this new facility was planned and built to house 
a secondary school and a college campus under one roof.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>A joint project of School District #42, Douglas College, and the District of Maple Ridge, 
Thomas Haney Centre can accommodate up to 1,000 secondary and 450 college students. 
The union of secondary school and college allows students to progress uninterrupted from 
grade eight to the completion of a college diploma, university transfer courses, or other 
studies in the life-long learning continuum.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Secondary school students who are considering post-secondary education can enrich their 
programs by taking Douglas College courses at the same time as they work on their 
secondary program. Such an opportunity ensures a much easier transition from secondary 
school to college.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>As well as sophisticated academic features, the centre possesses a variety of recreational 
facilities.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3>For more information about School District No. #42, contact:</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p align=left><font size=3><img src="bulletweb.gif" align=top width=17 height=17> </font><a href="http://www.schdist42.bc.ca/"><font size=3>School District #42 Web Site</font></a><font size=3><br>
School District #42 Phone: <strong>(604) 463-4200</strong></font><font size=4> <br>
</font><font size=3>District Education Office Fax: <strong>(604)463-4181</strong></font><font size=4> <br>
