<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>The S.P.C.A.</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
<br>
<font color="#000000"><img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16></font><font size=3> </font><a href="your_pet.html"><font size=3>You &amp; Your Pet in Maple Ridge</font></a></td><td align=right><img src="spca_dog.jpg" align=bottom width=117 height=118></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left><font color="#000000"><font size=4>S</font><font size=3><strong>ociety for Prevention of Cruelty to Animals<br>
</strong></font></font><font size=4><b>(S.P.C.A.)</b></font> <br>
10235 Industrial Avenue, Telephone 463-9511<br>
<br>
The Society for Prevention of Cruelty to Animals is a society, funded by private donations. 
Throughout British Columbia there are 34 branches of the S.P.C.A. In the Lower Mainland 
there are nine (9) shelters as well as the Vancouver Clinic. Your donations are needed to 
carry on the day-to-day work of animal rescue, shelter, and adoption as well as cruelty 
investigation. These donations are tax deductible.<br>
<br>
In Maple Ridge the S.P.C.A. responds to 2,500 calls for help (not including calls for 
information) every year. Approximately 2,300 animals needed our assistance in 1995.<br>
<br>
Here are some of the ways we serve animals and our communities:</p>
<ul>
<li>Investigate and prosecute cases of abuse, neglect, and cruelty. </li>
<li>Shelter homeless and unwanted animals and find them loving homes. </li>
<li>Promote and carry out spaying and neutering of animals to reduce pet 
overpopulation. </li>
<li>Rescue animals injured or in distress. </li>
<li>Return lost animals to owners. </li>
<li>Lobby for legislation to improve conditions for all animals. </li>
<li>Provide animal care advice to the public and humane education programs to schools. </li>
<li>Work to reduce use of animals in research. </li>
<li>Inspect establishments such as stables and pet stores. </li>
</ul>
<p>With your support we can make this a better world for animals and for people too. By 
preventing cruelty, we are creating a more humane and sustainable society. <br>
</p>
<p align=left><font size=4><b>Services</b></font><font size=5><b><br>
</b></font></p>
<ul>
<li>Animal Adoptions </li>
<li>Animal Rescues </li>
<li>Complaints/Investigations (cruelty, licence, nuisance violations) </li>
<li>Dog Licensing </li>
<li>Humane Euthanasia </li>
<li>Lost and Found </li>
<li>Low Cost Spay/Neuter Program </li>
<li>Operation Tattoo Program </li>
<li>Pet Pal Program </li>
<li>Stray and Deceased Animal Pick-up </li>
</ul>
<p>The S.P.C.A. is open seven days a week:<br>
</p>
<table>
<tr><td width=319>Monday - Friday</td><td width=319></td></tr>
<tr><td width=319>9 a.m. to 6 p.m. </td><td width=319>- Office Hours </td></tr>
<tr><td width=319>12 p.m. to 5:30 p.m.</td><td width=319>- Viewing &amp; Adoptions </td></tr>
<tr><td width=319></td><td width=319></td></tr>
<tr><td width=319>Saturday, Sunday and All Holidays</td><td width=319></td></tr>
<tr><td width=319>9 a.m. to 5 p.m.</td><td width=319>- Office Hours </td></tr>
<tr><td width=319>12 p.m. to 4:30 p.m. </td><td width=319>- Viewing &amp; Adoptions </td></tr>
</table>
<p><b>For after hours Emergencies Call 879-7343<br>
</b></p>
<p align=center><i>*The preceding information is available in a pamphlet at the District of Maple Ridge.</i> </p>
<p><font size=3><br>
</font></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
