<font size=3>This section will give you a few pointers in how to effectively 
navigate this site. There are certain elements and menus that will 
aid you in telling you where you are going and where you've been.<b> </b></font></td><td align=right valign=top><img src="navigation_main.gif" align=bottom width=109 height=147></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left><strong>The Main Menu Bar<br>
</strong><font size=3>You've probably noticed that every page of this site has a menu bar at the top. That menu 
bar will quickly take you to any of the main categories in district.maple-ridge.bc.ca. There 
are some sub-menus (on most pages, not this one) to choose from under the main menu.<br>
If at any time you get lost, just select the menu bar section in which your interest was, and 
you will soon be back on track.<br>
<br>
<strong>Link Icons<br>
</strong>Ever been to a web site and suddenly, without any indication, you found yourself 
somewhere else? This site has been constructed with easily identifiable icons that will tell 
you what your click will actually do. See below for explanations.</font> </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1 cellpadding=8 cellspacing=3 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top width=33%><font size=3><img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> If you see this maple 
leaf next to a link, it means 
you are going to a page 
within the District of 
Maple Ridge Web Site.</font></td><td valign=top width=33%><img src="email_leaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> This maple leaf next to 
a link means it will bring 
up an email box ready to 
mail to whoever's name 
you just clicked on.</td><td width=34%><img src="bulletweb.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=17> The little globe means 
that the link next to it will 
take you to a site that is 
outside of the District of 
Maple Ridge Web Site.</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=left>&#160; </p>
</td></tr>
</table>
