<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Our Neighbours</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td width=400><font size=5><strong><u>Our Neighbours</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
<br>
<font size=3><b><img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> </b></font><a href="welcome.html"><font size=3><b>Welcome</b></font></a><font size=3><b> <img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> </b></font><a href="climate.html"><font size=3><b>Climate</b></font></a><font size=3><b> <img src="bulletleaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> </b></font><a href="location.html"><font size=3><b>Location<br>
<br>
</b></font></a><font size=3>The District of Pitt Meadows, our immediate neighbour to the 
west, is known as the Gateway to the Fraser Valley. An energetic 
young community, Pitt Meadows' population has increased 21% 
from the 1991 census, to an estimated 1996 population of 14,500. 
The principal activity is agriculture, which absorbs 60% of Pitt 
Meadows' 51.5 square kilometre area.</font></td><td align=right valign=top><img src="ourneighbours_main.jpg" align=bottom width=120 height=185></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3>The landscape boasts a beauty conducive to a variety of recreational activities, and urban 
amenities have grown accordingly. Excellent schools, a library, churches, health care 
facilities, financial institutions, and affordable housing round out the package. A town centre 
recreation complex is being planned by Ridge Meadows Parks and Leisure Services.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>The District of Mission, lying 26 km east of Maple Ridge, is a community forested by tree 
farms covering 75% of the land base. This promotes Mission's appearance of being a single 
expansive park. There are also many shake and shingle mills in the area. Mission is a 
community that appreciates the Arts as well, hosting a Folk Music Festival each summer.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Fraser Valley growth has extended out to Mission, whose 1995 estimated population figure 
of 31,500 mirrors an impressive 18.4% increase over the 1991 census figures. Residential 
growth is complemented by a healthy supply of amenities: schools, post-secondary 
institutions, cultural, recreational, and religious facilities.</font><font size=4> </font></p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>

