<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Budget</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>1997 Provisional Budget </u></strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
<font size=2></font><p><font size=2></font>&nbsp;</p>
<p><font size=2>For your information, Council has approved the 1997 Budget packages. The Budget 
calls for a 3% increase in taxation. The key points on which the Budget were based 
upon are as follows: </font></p>
</td><td align=center valign=top><img src="anihorse.gif" align=bottom width=95 height=71><br>
<img src="clckbody.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=76><br>
<img src="pendulum.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=52></td></tr>
</table>
<p><font size=2><i>1997 budget projections are based on the following:</i></font> </p>
<ul>
<li><font size=2>Inflation will remain below 2.5%.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Unemployment will remain high at 9-10%.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Provincial growth will continue at a sluggish pace of 1%.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Maple Ridge will experience a modest increase in building starts over 1996.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Interest rates will remain low and therefore, reduce our investment return.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Municipal revenue declined $1.8 million, vs. 1996 budget figures. This is a result of reduced 
Provincial Government grants, lower income due to declining interest rates, and reduced 
building and development activity.</font> </li>
</ul>
<p><font size=2><i>The key points of the 1997 Provisional Budget are as follows:</i></font> </p>
<ul>
<li><font size=2>Municipal property taxation to be increased by 3%; this is forecast to generate $550,000; the 
cost to the average home will be $22.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Water rate increase of $10.00 to residential properties with an equivalent increase in rates to 
metered properties.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Real growth (new properties on the tax role) is projected at 3% and forecast to generate 
$561,400.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>User fees (building permits, leisure fees, etc.) to increase 5% to more closely recover the cost of 
the service.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>RCMP fee for false alarms to generate $24,000; this will also act to encourage owners to inspect 
their systems and reduce non-productivity of the Police Department.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Capital expenditures funded by General Taxation reduced by approximately 2% or $383,000. 
(Effectively, projects will be moved further into future years).</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Transfer from Accumulated Surplus of $304,300; $200,000 is to act as a stabilization baseline for 
the decline in interest income and $104,300 to smooth one-time future revenues.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Reduced Transfer to Reserve for Building Infrastructure of $456,800.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Implement Burning Permit Fee ($41,200) to finance the cost of the branch chipping program. This 
will effectively reduce wood waste and provide an alternative to outdoor burning.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Recycling of plastics will be introduced without a fee increase.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Four full-time vacant staff positions and numerous part-time positions eliminated for a savings 
of more than $225,000 (also $107,000 for other positions).</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Fire Department is the recipient of additional funding for member services and changes in 
administration of life insurance.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Police Services costs to remain at the 1996 level. Additional funding has been made available for 
a School Liaison Officer under a cost sharing arrangement with the School District and Pitt 
Meadows Municipality.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Funding has been identified for an Environmental Coordinator. This provision is contingent on 
a number of items that will require further analysis.</font> </li>
<li><font size=2>Cost saving service level reductions have been necessary in many of our Public Works 
operations. These are in the form of lengthened maintenance cycles (ditch cleaning, brushing, 
etc.). It is recognized that some will be noticeable, however, they are fiscally necessary.</font> </li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>

