<p><font size=5><strong><u>Bob Robertson</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>Chief Administrative Officer</u></font> </p>
<table width=100%>
<tr><td valign=top width=150><img src="bob_robertson.jpg" align=bottom width=144 height=188></td><td valign=top width=400><font size=3>Bob Robertson assumed the Chief Administrative Officer's 
position with the Municipality last Spring. Prior to joining the 
District of Maple Ridge, he was City Manager in Grande Prairie, 
Alberta. Bob also worked for a number of years in Fredericton, 
New Brunswick, first as Director of Planning and Development 
and then as Assistant City Administrator. <br>
<br>
In his role as Chief Administrative Officer, Bob coordinates staff 
functions, provides advice to Council, and formulates long range 
strategic and corporate business plans. He holds professional 
designations as a Member, American Institute of Certified 
Planners; Member, Canadian Institute of Planners; Member, 
Certified Economic Developers. He is completing a Ph.D. at 
Stirling University, Scotland.</font><font size=2><br>
<br>
</font><font size=3>e-mail </font><img src="email_leaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16><font size=3> </font><a href="mailto:bob_robertson@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca"><font size=3>Bob_Robertson@District.Maple-Ridge.bc.ca</font></a><font size=3> </font></td></tr>
</table>
