where he has held the positions of Accounting Manager, Deputy 
Treasurer, Treasurer and Director of Finance before assuming the 
position of General Manager: Corporate Services in 1994. Prior 
to coming to work for the District he worked for the Township of 
Esquimalt and was part of the Management Training Program for 
the Bank of Montreal. Richard is a Certified General Accountant, 
a Professional Manager with the Canadian Institute of 
Management and is a founding member and a Past President of 
the British Columbia Government Finance Officers' Association.<br>
<br>
Corporate Services is one of four divisions of the Municipal 
organization. The division is supported by a series of departments 
or functions as follows: Finance, Personnel, Computer 
Information Systems, Administrative Services (incl. Council 
Secretariat, Municipal Clerk, Legal Services Management), 
Bylaw Enforcement/Animal Control, Land Purchase/Sales and 
Rental Property Management, Police Services - (budget matters 
&amp; municipal personnel), and Community &amp; Business Relations.</font><font size=4>&#160; </font><font size=3><br>
