<p><font size=5><strong><u>Mike Murray</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>General Manager - Parks &amp; Community Services</u></font> </p>
<table width=100%>
<tr><td valign=top width=150><img src="mike_murray.jpg" align=bottom width=146 height=190></td><td valign=top width=400><font size=3>An employee of the Municipality for 19 years, Mike started in 
1977 as the Recreation Superintendent, and then became the 
Director of Parks and Recreation in 1981. Mike is the past 
president of the Professional Recreation Society of British 
Columbia, the British Columbia Recreation and Parks 
Association, and the Haney Rotary Club, and was awarded the 
British Columbia Recreation and Parks Association Citation for 
Outstanding Achievement in 1994.<br>
<br>
Mike assumed the position of General Manager of Parks and 
Community Services in 1994 and is responsible for the provision 
of Parks and Leisure Services in both Maple Ridge and Pitt 
Meadows, with direction provided through a tri-party Parks and 
Leisure Services Commission involving representatives from both 
Municipal Councils and the School Board. <br>
<br>
The division is also responsible for Emergency Social Service 
Planning, maintaining all Municipal Buildings, Public Library, and 
liaison with School District 42. Long range planning, policy 
development, and organizational development and coordination 
are areas of focus, for both the Parks and Leisure Services 
Division and the Municipality in general, in cooperation with the 
rest of the Senior Management Team.<br>
<br>
