<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Municipal Services</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Heritage Awards</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><p><font size=3><br>
The District of Maple Ridge Heritage Award program recognizes significant 
contributions to heritage conservation in the Municipality.<br>
</font></p>
<p><font size=3>The program is coordinated by the Heritage Advisory Committee and the 
Awards are made during Heritage Week in mid-February. <br>
</font></p>
</td><td align=center valign=top><font size=3><img src="anihorse.gif" align=bottom width=95 height=71><br>
<img src="clckbody.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=76><br>
<img src="pendulum.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=52></font></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p><font size=3>There are three categories for Heritage Awards:</font> </p>
<ol>
<li><font size=3>Heritage Achievement Award - To honour an individual, corporation, or organization 
for outstanding achievement in support of heritage conservation in the District of 
Maple Ridge. </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Residential Heritage Award - To honour the outstanding conservation of a residential 
heritage building or its landscaping in the District of Maple Ridge.</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Commercial/Institutional Heritage Award - To honour the outstanding conservation 
of a commercial or institutional heritage building or its landscaping in the District of 
Maple Ridge. </font></li>
</ol>
<p><font size=3>Nominations in the Residential and Commercial/Institutional categories can include 
photographs, plans, drawings and/or other relevant information although these are not 
required.</font> </p>
<p><font size=3>Guidelines:</font> </p>
<ol>
<li><font size=3>Awards may be given to projects, activities, groups or individuals who have 
furthered the goal of heritage conservation in the District of Maple Ridge. </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Awards will be presented during Heritage Week each year.</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Nominations must be submitted on the standard nomination form provided by the 
District of Maple Ridge. A photograph, site plan, drawing, and/or other relevant 
information is desirable but not mandatory. </font></li>
<li><font size=3>The criteria for evaluating nominated building projects will include quality of 
workmanship, appropriate design of any alterations or new additions, and the level of 
intervention with the heritage fabric of the building. </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Awards will be selected by the Heritage Awards Committee. </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Awards will be presented by the Council of the District of Maple Ridge.</font></li>
<li><font size=3>The Heritage Awards Committee will be composed of three members as follows:<br>
i) two members from the Heritage Advisory Committee;<br>
ii) one person appointed by the Heritage Advisory Committee.</font></li>
<li><font size=3>The Awards Committee can elect not to grant an award in any category in any given 
year. </font></li>
</ol>
<p><font size=3>For more information on the District of Maple Ridge Heritage Awards or the Heritage 
Advisory Committee please contact the Planning Department at <br>
</font><img src="email_leaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16> <a href="mailto:sharon_folkes@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca">sharon_folkes@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca</a> </p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

</html>

