<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Total Quality Management Survey </u></strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u><br>
District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
<br>
The following survey was recently (Fall 1996) circulated to members of 
the Canadian Association of Municipal Administrators (CAMA). The 
survey, supported by CAMA, is aimed at developing an empirical base of 
information about the use of Total Quality Management similar in scope to 
those surveys recently undertaken in both the United States and the United 
Kingdom. Any questions about the survey should be directed to Mr. R.W. 
Robertson, Chief Administrative Officer, District of Maple Ridge, 11995 
Haney Place, Maple Ridge, B.C. Canada V2X 6A9 <br>
Phone: (604) 463-5221 Fax: (604) 467-7329 or <br>
e-mail <img src="email_leaf.gif" align=bottom width=17 height=16><a href="mailto:bob_robertson@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca">bob_robertson@district.maple-ridge.bc.ca</a></td><td align=center valign=top><img src="anihorse.gif" align=bottom width=95 height=71><br>
<img src="clckbody.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=76><br>
<img src="pendulum.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=52></td></tr>
</table>
<p align=center>&#160; <font size=5><b>Total Quality Management<br>
and<br>
Local Government in Canada</b></font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table border=1 cellpadding=6 cellspacing=1 width=549>
<tr><td valign=top colspan=2><p align=center><font size=4>&#160; <b>Total Quality Management <br>
</b></font><font size=2><b>Definition of Relevant Terms*</b></font> </p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Customer</b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>Groups or individuals who rely on the organization&#146;s products and/or services.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Investor</b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>An individual or group who has injected their resources into the organization 
(includes shareholders and funding bodies).</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Key 
Processes </b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>Those processes that have a major impact on customer satisfaction and are critical 
to the success of the organization; they are usually cross functional and require 
constant attention.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Mission 
Statement</b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>Declaration of the fundamental purpose and aim of the organization; the 
fundamental reason for the existence of the organization.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Process </b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>A set of activities which occurs repeatedly and is organized to achieve a desired 
outcome</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Total Quality 
Management 
(TQM)</b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>A comprehensive, customer-focused system to improve the &quot;quality&quot; of products 
and services by involving employees at all levels throughout the organization.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Values</b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>Principles followed to guide behaviour in the future (desired state).</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=16%><font size=2><b>Vision </b></font></td><td valign=top width=84%><font size=2>What an organization intends to be in the future, its desired state</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top colspan=2><font size=1>* Source: National Quality Institute, Entry Guide for the Canada Awards for Excellence Ottawa, ON (1995).</font></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
