Chair: Councillor J. Clements </i></b></p>
<p>07.02.01 <br>
Disbursements for Month Ended November 30, 1996<br>
Staff report dated December 12, 1996 recommending that the subject Disbursements be 
authorized in the amount of $4,088,417.62.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>07.02.02 <br>
Sewer Area &quot;A&quot; - Inclusion of Nine Properties at 132 Avenue and 240 Street By-law No. 
5508-1996 <br>
Staff report dated December 10, 1996 recommending that Maple Ridge Sewer &quot;A&quot; Works 
Construction and Loan Authorization Amending By-law No. 5508-1996 be given three 
readings.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>07.02.03<br>
Adjustments to 1996 Collector's Roll<br>
Staff report dated December 5, 1996 recommending that an adjustment to the Collector's 
Roll be authorized to reflect a net increase in taxes receivable in the amount of $11,253.69 
of which the Municipal share is $5373.89.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>07.02.04<br>
Columbus Charities Association Shamrock Drive - March 13, 14 and 15, 1997 - Request 
for Approval<br>
Staff report dated December 20, 1996 recommending approval of the above noted 
request.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>07.02.05 <br>
Heart and Stroke Foundation of B.C. &amp; Yukon - Door to Door Canvass - Month of 
February, 1997 - Request for Approval<br>
Staff report dated December 18, 1996 recommending approval of the subject request.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
