<p>08.02.01 <br>
Building By-law <br>
Staff report dated December 29, 1996 recommending that Maple Ridge Building By-law 
No. 5451-1996 be granted first and second reading and further reviewed prior to further 
consideration.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation<br>
<br>
</p>
<p>08.03 <b><i>Planning Recommendations - Chair: Councillor T. Baker</i></b> </p>
<p>08.03.01 <br>
RZ/26/96 - Former Pacific Vocational Institute Site - P-6 to RS-2 and P-1 <br>
Staff report dated December 10, 1996 in response to Committee's request for additional 
information. (A staff report dated November 8, 1996, which is also attached, 
recommended that the application proceed to Public Hearing and was deferred at the 
December 9, 1996 Committee Meeting.<br>
</p>
<p><b>The Committee concurred with an amended recommendation that the application 
be forwarded to Public Hearing provided that the public is made aware there is 
likely to be a rezoning of lands to the north to Industrial and also made aware that 
the Municipality is commencing a study of the northern sector.<br>
</b></p>
<p>08.03.02<br>
RZ/32/96 - 28730 Lougheed Highway - RS-3 to M-2<br>
Staff report dated December 20, 1996 recommending that the subject application to permit 
an Industrial use be forwarded to Public Hearing subject to the conditions specified in the 
report.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>08.03.03 <br>
RZ/33/96 - 9796 - 287 Street and Property Directly to the South - RS-3 to M-2<br>
Staff report dated December 16, 1996 recommending that the subject application to permit 
the storage of lumber/expansion of an existing mill site be forwarded to Public Hearing 
subject to the conditions specified in the report.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>08.03.04 <br>
RZ/44/96 - 22631 - 119 Avenue - RS-1 to C-3<br>
Staff report dated December 19, 1996 recommending that the application for a cinema 
complex and retail space at ground level and residential units on the upper three levels be 
forwarded to Public Hearing subject to the conditions specified in the report.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>08.03.05<br>
DVP/39/96 - 12070 Dover Street<br>
Staff report dated December 19, 1996 recommending that the subject application to permit 
relaxations in the rear yard setback and minimum building envelope dimensions be 
considered at the January 28, 1997 Council Meeting.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>08.03.06 <br>
DP/30/96 -11961 - 203 Street<br>
Staff report dated December 19, 1996 recommending that the subject application to permit 
a veterinary hospital and caretaker suite be executed.<br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
<p>08.03.07<br>
Addition of Trees to Tree Protection By-law - Vicinity of 124 Avenue - By-law No. 
5518-1996<br>
Staff report dated December 18, 1996 recommending that Maple Ridge Tree Protection 
Amending By-law No. 5518-1996 be granted three readings, a public information meeting 
be held, etc. <br>
The Committee concurred with the recommendation.<br>
</p>
