<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Purchasing</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
</td><td align=center valign=top><br>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p align=center><font size=5><b>How to Sell to the District of Maple Ridge</b></font></p>
<p>The goal of the Purchasing Division of the Corporation of the District of Maple Ridge is to 
procure Goods and Services for the Municipality which represent the &quot;Best Value&quot; for the 
Municipality and all its taxpayers. Best value includes many characteristics including but not 
limited to: availability, suitability, serviceability, transportation, required training, warranty, 
design, overall life cycle cost implications, and other significant applicable characteristics. 
With each individual purchase these characteristics can change. </p>
<p>The types of goods and services we procure are too numerous to list in full, but some 
examples are: vehicles, heavy duty equipment, parts, pipe, road installation, water and 
sewer services, computer equipment, office products and machines, office furniture, 
consulting services, building and grounds maintenance services, communications, safety 
supplies, fire fighting apparatus and equipment, first aid supplies, drafting supplies, printing 
services, signage, janitorial, electrical, and the list goes on and on. </p>
<p>Some goods and services are purchased repetitively, others rarely. </p>
<p><font size=4><b>How does a supplier get on the Bidder's List? </b></font></p>
<p>All we ask is that you send us something in writing so we know you're out there. The 
written submission should include: </p>
<ul>
<li>Company name </li>
<li>Contact person </li>
<li>Address, phone number, and facsimile number </li>
<li>A brief description of the products or services available </li>
<li>Length of time in business </li>
<li>Any other information about the business you wish to include </li>
<li>A business card if available </li>
</ul>
<p>Optional submissions: </p>
<ul>
<li>Product brochures and catalogues are also accepted </li>
<li>References </li>
</ul>
<p>Once this information is received, the Purchasing Division will file it in our library of 
commodities for future reference and pass on information to other departments who may be 
interested in the new companies or products/services. <br>
</p>
<p align=center><font size=4><b><i>N.B. </i></b></font><font size=3><b><i>Your business must have a valid Business Licence for the city or 
municipality in which the work is being performed. <br>
</i></b></font></p>
<p><font size=3><b><i><br>
</i></b></font><font size=4><b>What If I am a Contractor or Service Company doing business on 
Municipal Properties? </b></font></p>
<p>As well as a valid business licence, you may be required to give proof of the following: </p>
<ul>
<li>An active Workers' Compensation Number or a Clearance letter from the Workers' 
Compensation Board </li>
<li>Minimum $2 million liability insurance with the Corporation of the District of Maple 
Ridge named as additional insured (details available) </li>
<li>Employee criminal checks where necessary </li>
<li>Federal, Provincial or Municipal Permits when and where applicable </li>
</ul>
<p>In many cases we will ask that your employees wear suitable identification and are aware of 
our health and safety standards. </p>
<p align=center><font size=4><b>Purchasing Contacts: <br>
<br>
</b></font><b>Earl Oddstad, Manager of Procurement</b> <font size=2><b><br>
(604) 467-7320 <br>
