<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Municipal Services</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="government/../Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><font size=5><strong><u>Inaugural Address</u></strong></font> &#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge<br>
<br>
</u></font><font size=3>The following is the Mayor's Inaugural Address presented at the Monday, 
December 2, 1996 meeting of Council: <br>
<br>
</font>I welcome all of you to this inaugural meeting of Council. First, I would like 
to thank the people of Maple Ridge for the support given me and the 
elected Councillors at the polls on November 16,1996. As a Council, we 
are aware of our responsibility to serve all people of Maple Ridge and we 
will do our best to justify the confidence placed in us.</td><td align=center valign=top><img src="anihorse.gif" align=bottom width=95 height=71><br>
<img src="clckbody.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=76><br>
<img src="pendulum.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=52></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p>I would like to congratulate Jim Clements, Candace Gordon and Betty Levens on their 
re-election. To Linda King, Ken Stewart, and Tom Baker - congratulations on winning a 
seat on Council. I hope your involvement in Municipal Government will be rewarding. To all 
of you, welcome to the 1996 to 1999 Municipal Council. Each of you has a great deal to 
offer and I look forward to our successful association and to providing good government to 
the citizens of Maple Ridge. </p>
<p>To retiring Councillor Jon Harris - you will be missed; but you can take satisfaction from 
knowing that you served your community well. I know you have always given your best. 
On behalf of the citizens of Maple Ridge, I thank you for your contribution to the provision 
of good government for our community.<br>
</p>
<p>Thank you to Councillors Ernie Day and Franz Prokop for your service to the community 
over the past three years. Your contributions will be part of building our complete 
community.<br>
</p>
<p>To the other candidates who were unsuccessful in the election, I know you will continue 
your community involvement.<br>
</p>
<p>Council business is transacted at the Council table. Council established two standing 
committees to deal with recommendations to Council on broad policy-related matters. I will 
continue the process with some minor changes. </p>
<p>The Corporate and Community Services, and Planning and Operational Committees, will 
remain. Each Committee will be made up of three Councillors.<br>
</p>
<p>The Committee of the Whole will have two sub-committees: a Budget Committee to deal 
with annual and long range financial plans and a Labour Relations Committee to focus on a 
new collective agreement that will be negotiated in the first quarter of 1997.<br>
</p>
<p>The Council meetings will continue to be held in the evenings - generally the second and 
fourth Tuesdays of the month. Meetings of Council In Camera will be held Monday 
afternoons as will the Council/Staff meetings that are used to work on completing our goals 
and objectives. A schedule of meetings for 1997 will be available.<br>
</p>
<p>We will continue with two special purpose citizens&iacute; committees to provide 
recommendations to Council on how certain issues should be handled.<br>
</p>
<p>1. Transit Service Review:<br>
</p>
<p>To be chaired by Councillor Baker and to have representation from Whonnock, Webster&iacute;s 
Corners, Hammond, Albion, Yennadon, and two people from the Core Area. I ask the 
Chair of this Committee to keep informed of actions taken, or proposed, by the Vancouver 
Regional Transit Commission and to provide advice about levels of transit services needed 
by our residents. </p>
<p>2. Air Quality Review: <br>
</p>
<p>To be chaired by Councillor Gordon and have representation from Whonnock, Webster&iacute;s 
Corners, Hammond, Silver Valley, Albion, the Core, and three members from the Urban 
Area. Two bylaws that are currently under review are the Burning Bylaw and the Smoking 
Bylaw.<br>
</p>
<p>One of our goals will be the construction of a new animal shelter during the next year. 
Councillor Clements and I will work with the GVRD to follow up on previous plans at 
Kanaka Creek Park.<br>
</p>
<p>I am also asking Councillors Levens and King to co-chair a committee to address the 
Library/Cultural/Theatre issue in the downtown area. I will set aside $2 million for future 
development from sale of lands, and will ask volunteers and fund-raisers to set aside a goal 
for a three-year period.<br>
</p>
<p>In Planning we have completed the Official Community Plan. Eighteen months of work 
completed the first major review in 12 years. This will set the guidelines for the next decade.<br>
</p>
<p>I am very pleased that we have an Advisory Design Panel to review developments and I 
will assign Councillor Stewart as the liaison from Council. <br>
</p>
<p>The 1997 Budget deliberations will focus on: </p>
<ul>
<li>enhancing environmental protection </li>
<li>water to the east end of Maple Ridge </li>
<li>a chipping and composting site as a top priority. </li>
</ul>
<p>As Mayor, I am very pleased with our working arrangement with Pitt Meadows. The Joint 
Leisure Service Agreement is working very well. We are also considering future 
partnerships which could include Pitt Meadows Airport. <br>
</p>
<p>Our Finance Department has, over the past three consecutive years, received the Canadian 
Award for Financial Reporting as well as the Award for Distinguished Budget Presentation.<br>
</p>
<p>Our debt per capita in 1993 was $400 and in 1996 is $300.<br>
</p>
<p>Downtown development is very important to our community. We have committed to a 25% 
reduction of Development Cost Charges in the Core and have set aside funds for 
streetscape improvements. There will be a Downtown Action Plan to recruit business and 
streamline regulations.<br>
</p>
<p>I want to see a plan for beautification and care of Maple Ridge to make it a complete 
community open for business, making jobs available, and ensuring funds are available for 
the health and safety of our community. <br>
</p>
<p>This Council will establish formal goals and objectives by developing a business plan for the 
Corporation and ensuring that the public interest is being served. We have scheduled 
meetings during December 1996 to start the process. I hope to have a completed set of 
goals and an implementation schedule before the end of 1997. Council and staff will meet 
every second week to exchange information and collectively work to achieve our goals.<br>
</p>
<p>I expect Councillors to be informed of all discussions affecting the Municipality. When 
Councillors meet with individuals or agencies relating to Council business, a brief written 
report must be submitted to the other Council members.<br>
</p>
<p>I want our Seniors to be safe and to feel safe in Maple Ridge. I will continue to work 
closely with Community Law Enforcement and the Seniors to make sure their safety is 
assured. <br>
</p>
<p>I look forward to this Council working together as a team. We will not always agree on all 
issues, but I expect each Councillor to deal with the issues not the personalities. By working 
together, we will accomplish our goals and provide good government for our citizens. I will 
not, at this time, direct Councillors to work on my priorities, other than the one that 
establishes our goals and objectives. I hope we can work together to accomplish our goals 
and objectives and our joint goals for our community.<br>
</p>
<p>I invite our residents to take an active interest in their municipality. With sufficient 
involvement from our citizens, we will make Maple Ridge a better community for us all. 
Over the next three years, I intend to hold public forums in the various communities to listen 
to the views of as many people as possible. Early next year we will set a schedule for these 
meetings.<br>
</p>
<p>I wish each of you here today and all the citizens of Maple Ridge a happy, healthy and 
prosperous New Year.<br>
<br>
Respectfully submitted,</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Carl E. Durksen<br>
Mayor<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

