<html>

<head>
<title>District of Maple Ridge - Budget News Release</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#800000" vlink="#808080" alink="#FFFF00" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<div align=center><center>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=550>
<tr><td><p align=center><a href="home.html"><font size=2><img src="home.gif" alt="Home" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="tourism.html"><font size=2><img src="tourism_icon.gif" alt="Tourism" align=bottom width=88 height=20></font></a><a href="government.html"><font size=2><img src="government_icon.gif" alt="Government" align=bottom width=100 height=20></font></a><a href="business.html"><font size=2><img src="busines_icon.gif" alt="Business" align=bottom width=80 height=20></font></a><a href="localnews.html"><font size=2><img src="localnews_icon.gif" alt="Local News" align=bottom width=93 height=20></font></a><a href="contact.html"><font size=2><img src="Contact_icon.gif" alt="Contact" align=bottom width=79 height=20></font></a><font size=2> </font></p>
<table width=550>
<tr><td valign=top><p align=left><font size=5><strong><u>News Release</u></strong><strong> </strong></font>&#149; <font size=4><u>District of Maple Ridge</u></font><br>
<br>
<font size=3><b>Thursday, December 19, 1996</b></font></p>
<p align=left>Maple Ridge Municipal Council has completed the 1997 Provisional 
Budget process. Highlights of the budget include:</p>
<ul>
<li><p align=left>Municipal revenue is $1.8 million lower in 1997 than the 1996 
budget figures, this is the result of reduced provincial grants; lower 
levels of development activity; and lower interest rates. </p>
</li>
</ul>
</td><td align=center valign=top><img src="anihorse.gif" align=bottom width=95 height=71><br>
<img src="clckbody.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=76><br>
<img src="pendulum.gif" align=bottom width=58 height=52></td></tr>
</table>
<ul>
<li>Municipal tax rates will be increased by 3%, representing $22 to the average 
homeowner and a $10 charge for water use. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Four full-time vacant positions and a number of part-time positions have been 
eliminated. There are no new positions in the budget. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Capital construction for Municipal projects has been reduced by 2% and a small 
appropriation from reserves will be used in 1997. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>User fees (building permits, leisure fees) are projected to increase approximately five 
percent. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Council has directed staff to prepare a corporate, multi-year business plan for Maple 
Ridge that will review all revenues and expenditures and the delivery of services 
within the community. This process will begin immediately and will take 
approximately eight months to complete. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Council has instructed staff to prepare a business plan for the Fire Department that 
will review issues raised during the budget process about service delivery and the 
operating and capital cost structure. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Municipality will undertake specific business improvement projects aimed at 
enhancing service levels and reducing costs. </li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
</body>

