<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Student Services</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Housing</FONT></FONT></H2>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The University does not provide
on-campus housing for graduate students, and students are encouraged to
plan for accommodations before the semester begins. The Law School Admissions
Office provides a roommate list during the summer for first-year J.D. students
seeking to share accommodations. The Graduate Programs Office maintains
a similar list for incoming LL.M. students. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The University's Off-Campus
Housing Resource Center is available to assist students in finding housing.
The Resource Center is located on the fourth floor of the Marvin Center,
800 21st Street, N.W.There are a variety of local housing options for students,
including efficiencies, apartments, and group houses. Prices for housing
vary considerably and generally match those in other major metropolitan
areas. Though there is limited housing within walking distance of the school,
many students live in other parts of the city or in nearby suburbs and
take advantage of the excellent public transportation system in the metropolitan
area (which includes a subway stop on the GW campus). </FONT></FONT><A NAME="comp"></A></P>

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Computing Facilities</FONT></FONT></H2>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>All computing facilities
for student use within the Law School are located in the computer classroom
in the Jacob Burns Law Library. The classroom features 28 IBM-compatible
computers, which can be used for word processing, e-mail, and accessing
a variety of automated resources including the Internet, LEXIS and WESTLAW,
and the library s CD-ROM network. These computers are linked to free dot-matrix
printers; laser printing is available at cost. While the computer classroom
is available only to law students, additional computer facilities that
are available to all GW students are located around campus. These computer
labs feature both IBM-compatible and Macintosh computers. In addition to
the multi-task stations housed in the computer classroom, more than 40
computers located throughout the library are available for accessing particular
resources such as JACOB (the online catalog of the Jacob Burns Law Library),
the CD-ROM network, and LEXIS and WESTLAW. The library also has available
several laptop computers that can be checked out by law students. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The Law School strongly recommends
that students purchase a personal computer, a modem, and a printer to assist
them in their studies. In addition to using the computer to write papers,
students may conduct research using online resources. While personal computers
are available at the Law School to search databases, the number of stations
available for word processing are limited and may be unavailable at times
when they are being used for research or instruction. Although the Law
School has determined that it will be an IBM-compatible environment, both
Macintosh and IBM-compatible computers may be used successfully for word
processing and research purposes. Hardware and software may be purchased
at a substantial discount at GW's <A HREF="http://www.coco.gwu.edu">Colonial
Computers</A>, telephone (202) 994-9300. </FONT></FONT><A NAME="dis"></A></P>

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Disability Support Services</FONT></FONT></H2>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The Law School's Dean of
Students Office coordinates with the University's <A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/~dss/">Office
of Disability Support Services</A> to assure that the special services
necessary for disabled students to participate fully in their academic
programs and the extracurricular life of the campus are provided for them
through University and community resources. </FONT></FONT><A NAME="smith"></A></P>

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The Smith Center (Athletic
Facilities)</FONT></FONT></H2>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The Charles E. Smith Center
offers a wide variety of facilities for student use. In addition to basketball,
volleyball, racquetball and squash courts, there are rooms with universal
free weights, an eight-lane indoor pool, an indoor jogging track, two auxiliary
gymnasiums, and saunas. Recreational activities include club and intramural
sports, instructional sports clinics for pastimes such as weight training,
racquetball, and tennis, and fitness programs such as aerobics. </FONT></FONT><A NAME="health"></A></P>

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Health Insurance and Student
Health Service</FONT></FONT></H2>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The Student Health Service
is an outpatient clinic staffed by physicians, nurse practitioners, and
physician assistants who can evaluate and treat most of students' medical
problems. Charges may be incurred for labwork, immunization, allergy injections,
supplies, and medication. Psychiatric evaluation and short-term therapy
appointments and crisis intervention are available. Health education and
outreach programs on a variety of topics are provided throughout the year.
Students must be currently enrolled on campus in the University to receive
treatment at the Student Health Service. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1><B>Health and Accident Insurance</B>
</FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>The University recommends
that all students be covered by health and accident insurance. Information
on group health insurance options offered through the University is distributed
during orientation for incoming first-year students, or it may be obtained
by calling the GW Health Plan at (301)941-2000. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" HEIGHT=13 WIDTH=357> </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50></A>
</P>

