<head>
<title>The Career Development Office</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL">

<H3>Mission Statement</H3>

The goal of the Career Development Office (CDO) is to serve the needs of all students and
alumni of The George Washington University Law School through a variety of services
including, but not limited to, individual counseling, group seminars, self-assessment materials,
interviewing programs, a career resource library and the alumni network.  Our mission is to:
<p>
<center>
<h2>PREP</h2>
</center>
<p>
<font size=+3>P</font>repare students and alumni for the legal job market by:<br>
<DL>
	<DD>1) encouraging them to conduct self-assessment in an effort to focus their job search
	<DD>2) educating them on their legal and non-legal options in today's competitive legal market.
	
</DL>
<p>
<font size=+3>R</font>each out to employers and to GW law students and alumni to assist in meeting mutual
employment and career needs; organize interviewing programs, and offer specific programming
to reach students and alumni requiring career development.
<p>
<font size=+3>E</font>quip students and alumni with the necessary tools for the job search -- a career map; resume
and cover letter writing; job search strategy; employment and informational interview skills; and
networking techniques.
<p>
<font size=+3>P</font>rovide students with the appropriate career materials and resources for the job search through
a comprehensive Career Resource Library and a variety of handouts.

<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>

</body>

