<html>
<head>
<title>The Career Development Office</title>
</head>


<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL">

<H3>Services</H3>
                                            

The Career Development Office (CDO) provides a full range of services to support the career
decision-making process.  Students, graduates, and prospective employers are served through
access to job vacancy advertising, newsletters on current career information, individual and
group counseling on resume preparation, self-assessment, interviewing skills development and
job-search strategies, a career resource library, the Alumni Career Network, and seminars and
panel presentations covering legal career topics as well as alternative career options.  Students
are further served through significant employer-support programs such as fall campus
interviewing, off-campus regional interviewing, and spring interviewing.  For a full explanation
of the services the CDO offers, see the current Student and/or Alumni Handbook.

<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
</body>

</html>

