<head>
<title>The Career Development Office</title>
</head>


<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL">

<h3>Alumni Career Network</h3>

<h3>What is the Alumni Career Network?</h3>

<ul>
<li>A database of over 1,000 GW Law School alumni established to
assist students and fellow alumni with legal career information.

<li>Alumni provide information on practice areas, employers and
geographical areas.

<li>Alumni provide information on career alternatives.
</ul>

<h3>How does it work?</h3>

<ul>
<li>Law School alumni volunteer to serve as Alumni Resources.

<li>The Network is managed by the Alumni Career Network
Coordinator in the Career Development Office.

<li>Students and alumni seeking career information meet with a
career consultant to discuss goals and interests before they are
referred to Alumni Resources.

<li>The Career Development Office assesses the effectiveness and
appropriateness of each contact.

<li>An Alumni Resource will only be contacted four times within a
year.
</ul>

<h3>Why participate in the Network?</h3>

<ul>
<li>The Network provides an opportunity to be involved with
current students and fellow alumni of the GW Law School on a
personal level.

<li>The Network creates networking and informational interviewing
opportunities for students and alumni.

<li>The Network allows you to share information, advice and
experiences with students and fellow alumni.
</ul>

<h3>How do I join the Network?</h3>

<ul>
<li>Contact Jill Kirson, Alumni Network Coordinator, at <A HREF="mailto:jill@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu">Jill@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu</A> or (202) 994-7340 if you are interested in
accessing the Network.
</ul>


<p>

<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
