<html>
<head>
<title>The Career Development Office</title>
</head>


<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL">

<h3>Employer Information</h3>

<h3>Recruiting Options</h3>

The Career Development Office is dedicated to providing a variety
of recruiting options for all kinds of legal employers.  We offer
fall and spring interview programs and year-round job posting
services.  This year over two-hundred and fifty employers
participated in the Fall and Regional Interview Programs.  A
spring interview program, the Public Interest Interview Program,
and Small Firm Interviewing during the spring semester, will bring additional
employers on-campus.  And for those employers that do not
interview on-campus, our resume referral service is a viable
option.
<p>
<h3>The Public Interest Interview Program</h3>

The George Washington University Law School and Georgetown
University Law Center sponsor a Public Interest/Public Service
Recruitment Program for public interest employers to interview
law students from both schools for paid summer and volunteer
postitions and permanent positions.   For more information and registration materials please contact Kristen Marshall
at <A HREF="mailto:kristen@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu">kristen@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu</A>or (202) 994-7340.


<h3>The Small Firm Interview Program</h3>

For employers who recruit later in the school year and hire as
positions become available, the Career Development Office offers
in-house interview rooms for on-campus recruiting.  With a full
schedule, an employer may see up to twenty-one students in one
day.  Interviews are usually twenty or thirty minutes in length
and employers pre-screen one hundred percent of the students they
see. Interview rooms are available Monday through
Saturday during the spring semester.  For more information and registration materials please contact Kristen Marshall
at <A HREF="mailto:kristen@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu">kristen@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu</A>or (202) 994-7340.


<h3>The Fall Interview Program</h3>

The Fall Interview Program takes place during the month of
September.  Employers have the option of interviewing near the
law school campus or in their D.C. office.  Employers
participating in the program prescreen the students they
interview and determine the total number of students they see. 
The Career Development Office oversees all arrangements for the
interview day.

<h3>Regional Interview Programs</h3>

Employers who wish to interview students without all the time and
expense associated with traveling out-of-town participate in a
Regional Interview Program.  If a recruitment trip to Washington
is inconvenient, we strongly encourage employers to participate
in one of our Regional Interview Programs.  As with the Fall
Interview Program near campus, employers recruiting in regional
locations prescreen the students they interview.  This year plans
are underway for programs in Atlanta, Chicago, Los Angeles, New
York, Philadelphia, and San Francisco.   When program dates,
locations and other information is available, this site will be
updated.


<h3>Employer Registration</h3>

Employer registration for the Fall and Regional Interview
Programs will be accepted by mail or fax using a request form. 
This site will be updated with more information as it becomes available.

<h3>Resume Referrals</h3>
The Career Development Office will collect and forward resumes to
employers upon request during the fall and spring semester.  The
CDO will post the request, collect resumes from interested
students and forward them to employers.  Requests for a resume
referral are accepted by mail or fax.  Request letters must
include the following basic information about your hiring needs:
type of job; practice area for which you are hiring; if multiple
offices, locations for which you are hiring; student year
requested; hiring criteria; and organizational literature.  There
is no fee for a resume referral.

<h3>Job Announcements</h3>


Job announcements or job posting is a service the Career
Development Office offers year round free of charge.  Job
Announcements are made available to students and alumni in the
Career Development Office Resource Library and posted under one
or more of the categories listed below.


<h3>Job Announcement Categories</h3>

1997 Permanent-Permanent positions for 1997 graduates
<p>
1997 Summer-Positions for summer following first or second year
or third year for evening students
<p>
Recent Graduate-Permanent positions for graduates with zero to
one year of experience
<p>
Internship-Internship positions for which students earn academic
credit instead of monetary compensation for work performed at
government agencies, public interest and non-profit organizations
<p>
Clerkship-Summer positions or term appointments with judges for
graduates
<p>
Intellectual Property-Positions for students or graduates that   
require technical training and/or an undergraduate degree in
science, engineering or math
<p>
Government/Public Interest-Positions for students or graduates in

federal government, non-profit and public interest organizations
<p>
Alternative Careers-Positions that may or may not involve legal
work
<p>
Education-Teaching positions for graduates
<p>
DC Alumni-Positions in the D.C. area
<p>
Non-DC Alumni-Positions across the United States
<p>
Part-time-Part-time positions for students that require twenty
hours of work per week or less
<p>
Full-time-Full-time positions for students that require          
more than twenty hours of work per week.

<h3>How to Request a Job Announcement</h3>

Requests for job announcements are accepted by phone, fax or
mail.  For more information on posting a job, contact Rene
Lindsey, Job Posting Coordinator, at <A HREF="mailto:rene@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu">Rene@cdo.nlc.gwu.edu</A> or (202) 994-7340.
 
<p>

<p>
