<html>
<head>
<title>
GWLAW Inclement Weather Info
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>
<h5>GW Law School<br>
Records Office</h5><br><P>
<h4>Inclement Weather Info<br>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h4>
<p>
If the winter weather turns foul and threatens to close the school, please note the following:
<br><BR>
<center>**IF GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCES IT IS
CLOSING,<br>
THEN THE LAW SCHOOL SHALL ALSO CLOSE.**</center>
<br><P>
The first place to check for the status of the school is the University's Inclement Weather Hotline:
<center><h3>(202) 994-5050</h3></center>
<p><br>
Once it is announced that the University is closing, the Law School Records Office's Information
Hotline will
be updated with the same information as it applies to the Law School:
<center><h4>(202) 994-6260, then press option '7' </h4></center>

<I>NOTE:  GW usually does not close unless the federal government has closed.  
HOWEVER, GW has been known to stay open even though the federal government closes.</I>


<p><br>
<h5><i>Updated: 12/26/96</i><br>

<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h5>
</font>
<p>

