<head>
<TITLE>Entrance and Degree Requirements</TITLE>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>
<H2>Entrance and Degree Requirements</H2>

<H3>Entrance Requirements</H3>

To be considered for admission to the Juris Doctor degree program, a candidate must have earned a bachelor's degree from a regionally accredited college or university and must have taken the Law School Admission Test (LSAT) within the past three years.


<H3>Degree Requirements</H3>

In order to earn the Juris Doctor degree, students must satisfactorily meet the following academic requirements: Completion of 84 credit hours; fulfillment of the residence requirement; completion of the required curriculum; and maintenance of the minimum grade-point average of 1.67.



<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
