<TITLE>The First Year and the Required Curriculum</TITLE>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>
<h2>The First Year and the Required Curriculum</h2>
Each first-year student is assigned to a sec-tion of 85-120 students, and the section has its classes together throughout the first year. Students in a section thus get to know each other quite well and develop lasting friendships out of their first-year experience.The prescribed first-year curriculum is the foundation upon which all further legal study is built. In addition to the fundamental knowledge acquired in the traditional, substantive courses, students begin to develop important skills in the Legal Research and Writing and Introduction to Advocacy courses. These classes of approximately 12 students are co-taught by practicing attorneys and third-year law students. The third-year students, or Research Fellows, are selected at the end of their second year on the basis of demonstrated research and writing ability, communication skills, and commitment to teaching.The required curriculum is as follows:<P>FULL-TIME DAY DIVISION<BR>(First year)<BR><I>Fall semester</I><UL>	<LI>Torts	<LI>Contracts I	<LI>Civil Procedure I	<LI>Criminal Law	<LI>Legal Research and Writing</UL><I>Spring semester</I><UL>	<LI>Contracts II	<LI>Property	<LI>Constitutional Law I	<LI>Civil Procedure II	<LI>Introduction to Advocacy</UL><p>FULL-TIME DAY/EVENING DIVISION<BR>(First year)<BR><I>Fall semester</I><UL>	<LI>Contracts I	<LI>Torts	<LI>Civil Procedure I	<LI>Legal Research and Writing</UL><I>Spring semester</I><UL>	<LI>Contracts II	<LI>Constitutional Law I	<LI>Civil Procedure II	<LI>Criminal Law	<LI>Professional Responsibility and Ethics	<LI>Introduction to Advocacy</UL>(Second year)<br><I>Fall semester</I><UL>	<LI>Property</UL><p>PART-TIME EVENING DIVISION<BR>(First year)<BR><I>Fall semester</I><UL>	<LI>Contracts I	<LI>Torts	<LI>Legal Research and Writing</UL><I>Spring semester</I><UL>	<LI>Contracts II	<LI>Criminal Law	<LI>Constitutional Law I	<LI>Introduction to Advocacy</UL>(Second year)<BR><I>Fall semester</I><UL>	<LI>Property	<LI>Civil Procedure I	</UL><I>Spring semester</I><UL>	<LI>Civil Procedure II</UL>Additionally, upperclass students who attended the Full-Time Day or Part-Time Evening Division in the first year are required to take Professional Responsibility and Ethics, and all upperclass students must fulfill the two-credit legal writing requirement.
<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
