   <TITLE>Entrance and Degree Requirements</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H2><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Entrance and Degree Requirements</FONT></FONT></H2>

<H3><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Entrance Requirements</FONT></FONT></H3>

<H4><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>U.S. Law School Graduates</FONT></FONT></H4>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>For graduates of U.S. law
schools, a Juris Doctor or equivalent degree is required from a law school
that is accredited by the American Bar Association. The applicant must
have demonstrated a high degree of academic excellence in earning the first
law degree. Advanced standing is not granted for credit earned while a
candidate for the first law degree or for credit earned at other law schools.
</FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/llm_app.htm">Request
an application to the LL.M. program. </A></FONT></FONT></P>

<H4><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Foreign Law School Graduates</FONT></FONT></H4>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Foreign Law School Graduates
Applicants seeking admission to the International Legal Studies Program
must have earned a law degree with high academic standing from a duly accredited
law faculty of a foreign university. They must also demonstrate that they
have the requisite English language skills to undertake and complete their
studies. Advanced standing is not granted for credit earned while a candidate
for the first law degree or for credit earned at other institutions. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/llm_app.htm">Request
an application to the LL.M. program. </A></FONT></FONT></P>

<H3><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Degree Requirements</FONT></FONT></H3>

<H4><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>U.S. Law School Graduates</FONT></FONT></H4>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>To earn the Master of Laws
degree, candidates with a U.S. law degree must fulfill the following requirements:
Completion of 24 credit hours, including the prescribed number of credit
hours in courses in the field in specialized programs; attendance for a
residence period of not less than two consecutive semesters; achievement
of a cumulative grade-point average of 2.67 at the time all requirements
are met; completion and acceptance of a thesis; and completion of all requirements
at the Law School within one calendar year of matriculation for full-time
students and two calendar years for part-time students. </FONT></FONT></P>

<H4><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>Foreign Law School Graduates</FONT></FONT></H4>

<P><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>In order to earn the Master
of Laws degree, candidates in the International Legal Studies Program must
fulfill the following requirements: Completion of 24 credit hours, including
the prescribed number of credit hours in courses in the field in specialized
programs; attendance for a residence period of not less than two consecutive
semesters; achievement of a cumulative grade-point average of 2.33 at the
time all requirements are met; completion of all requirements at the Law
School within one academic year of matriculation for full-time students
and three academic years for part-time students; and completion and acceptance
of a thesis. In special circumstances, the thesis requirement may be waived
with the permission of the director of the International Legal Studies
Program. </FONT></FONT></P>

<P><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" HEIGHT=13 WIDTH=357><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>
</FONT></FONT></P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50></A><FONT FACE="HELVETICA,ARIAL"><FONT SIZE=-1>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><IMG SRC="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50></A>
</FONT></FONT></P>

</BODY>
