<head>
<title>Faculty Directory Cheryl D. Block</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>Cheryl D. Block</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Hofstra University; J.D., State University of New York at Buffalo<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Block joined the Law School faculty in 1985. She taught previously at the University of Missouri and University of New Mexico law schools. After grad-
uating from law school she clerked for 
the Honorable Kevin Thomas Duffy, U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York. She practiced tax law in New York City before beginning her teaching career. She has written numerous articles on taxation and more recently on public policy relating to federal bailouts and 
legislative voting rules. She is presently writing a book on corporate taxation for Little, Brown. Professor Block s pro bono activities have included serving as vice president and treasurer of Literacy Volun-teers of America, National Capital Area from 1989 to 1992. Professor Block was awarded the Distinguished Faculty Ser-vice Award by the 1992 graduating class.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
