<title>
Faculty Directory
Robert Brauneis
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_brauei.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=144>



<h3>
Robert Brauneis
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., University of California, Santa Cruz<BR> 
J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Brauneis joined the Law School faculty in 1993. After graduating from law school, he served as a law 
clerk to Judge Stephen G. Breyer of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the First Circuit (now Justice Breyer), and to Justice David H. Souter. Professor Brau-neis has also served as an assistant corporation counsel for the City of Chicago, con-
centrating in the areas of real estate 
and land-use regulation. His teaching interests include property, real estate transactions, land-use regulation and local government law.
<br>
</body>
