<title>
Faculty Directory
Naomi R. Cahn
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_cahn.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=144>



<h3>
Naomi R. Cahn
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Princeton University<BR> 
J.D., Columbia University<BR> 
LL.M., Georgetown University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Since graduating from law school in 1983, Professor Cahn has held a variety 
of positions in both the private and 
public interest sectors, including as 
an associate with the Washington, D.C. firm of Hogan & Hartson, and as a staff attorney with Philadelphia s Community Legal Services. For the five years prior to her joining the faculty of the Law School in 1993, Professor Cahn was the Assistant Director of the Sex Discrimination Clinic at Georgetown University Law Center. She was a visiting professor at Georgetown from 1991 to 1993. At the Law School, Professor Cahn teaches contracts, family law, and trusts and estates.
<br>
</body>
</html>
