<title>
Faculty Directory
W. Burlette Carter
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_carter.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=143>



<h3>
W. Burlette Carter
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law
B.A., Agnes Scott College<BR> 
J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>


After graduating from law school in 1985, Professor Carter joined the law firm of Hughes Hubbard & Reed as an associate. During her tenure there she practiced in both the New York and Washington, D.C., offices. Her work included such diverse areas as administrative law, antitrust, bankruptcy, employment discrimination, products liability, RICO, and savings and loan and securities litigation. Professor Carter is a member of the New York 
and District of Columbia bars.
<br>
</body>
