<html>
<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Lynn E. Cunningham
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Lynn E. Cunningham
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., Cornell University<BR> 
B.D., Union Theological Seminary<BR>
J.D., Columbia University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Cunningham worked for over 20 years as a legal services and public interest attorney in Washington, D.C.  Before coming to the Law School he 
was of counsel to the public interest 
law firm Terris Pravik & Wagner.  He briefly practiced with the National Housing Law Project before joining Neighborhood Legal Services in 1977.  While managing attorney of the Law Reform Unit, he conducted impact 
litigation in the areas of housing, welfare, and Medicaid in D.C. and elsewhere.  
He frequently testified at D.C. Council hearings on issues affecting low income residents.  In addition, he developed 
and participated in numerous training programs for legal services and pro 
bono programs both for national and local audiences.  His articles on impact 
litigation have appeared in the Clearing-house Review.  He compiled and edited a widely used reference manual on 
landlord-tenant law.  He is active in the D.C. Bar and was co-chair of the District of Columbia affairs section.  In 1994 Professor Cunningham was awarded 
the Stuart Stiller Award and the Jerrold Scoutt Prize in recognition of his service to legal services clients and the community.  An Episcopalian priest, he is a member of the adjunct clergy at St. Margaret s Episcopal Church in Washington, D.C.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
