<h3>Frank D. Durand
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Assistant Dean for Student Affairs<BR>
B.A., University of New Mexico; 
J.D., Stanford University
<p>
<p>


Dean Durand came to the Law School 
in 1991 from Denver, Colorado. There, 
he was in private practice, specializing 
in the areas of environmental and 
natural resources law. Dean Durand brings to the Law School administration the perspective of someone who has recently completed law school and made the transition to legal practice.
In addition to assisting Dean Robinson 
in administering law school programs and services, Dean Durand provides 
academic advisement to J.D. students, maintains day-to-day responsibility 
for students in the part-time evening 
program, and works with student organizations. He also serves on the D.C. Bar Continuing Legal Education Committee.
