<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_fitzge.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
Alice Sullivan Fitzgerald
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Clinical Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Boston College<BR>
J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Fitzgerald has taught in the field of clinical legal education since 1986.  After graduation from law school, Professor Fitzgerald joined the Law School s Administrative Advocacy clinical program, becoming the director in 1991.  She has been an active member of the District of Columbia Bar Continuing Legal Education program as a faculty member for Social Security Disability, public benefits, and administrative advocacy courses.  She has also been a volunteer attorney for the D.C. Bar Volunteer Lawyer s Project, representing indigent and elderly clients on a pro bono basis.  She continues to participate in a number of community and university-wide activities.  In 1995, Professor Fitzgerald became the director of the Law School s Outside Placement internship program, coordinating the placement of legal interns in judicial clerkships, government agencies, and public interest organizations.
<br>
</body>
