<h3>Katie Harrington-McBride
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Deputy Assistant Dean for Legal Research and Writing and Associate Professorial Lecturer in Law<BR>
B.A., J.D., George Washington University
<p>
<p>


Dean Harrington-McBride rejoined 
the administration of the Law School 
in 1994.  Having served as an adminis-
trative assistant in the dean s office 
while attending law school as an 
evening student during her first year, Dean Harrington-McBride gained a unique perspective on the Law School and its mission.  As a law student she served as secretary and then president 
of the Moot Court Board, was a student attorney in the Civil Litigation Clinic, 
and participated in both trial and appellate advocacy competitions.  During her third year, she pursued her interest in legal research and writing by serving 
as a Dean s Fellow, instructing first-year students in legal research methods.  
In her current role as an administrator and instructor in the Legal Research 
and Writing Program, Dean Harrington-McBride continues to work with first-year students to help them gain the fundamental writing skills they will need in practice.  In addition to her responsibilities in the writing program, she serves 
as the faculty adviser to the Moot Court Board, the Trial Court Board, and the Alternative Dispute Resolution Board.

<br>
</body>
