Faculty Directory
Carol L. Izumi
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_izumi.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=142>



<h3>
Carol L. Izumi
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., Oberlin College<BR>
J.D., Georgetown University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Before joining the full-time clinical law faculty in 1986, Professor Izumi served 
as law clerk to Judge Harriett R. Taylor 
of the D.C. Superior Court; specialized 
in civil litigation as an associate in a Washington, D.C., firm; and was assistant director of a Washington public interest organization. Professor Izumi s clinical programs at the Law School have been 
in the area of consumer law, including the Consumer Litigation Clinic and Consumer Mediation Clinic. Her teaching and research interests include alternative dispute resolution. In the fall of 1991, she assumed teaching responsibilities for the academic course in mediation. Professor Izumi is actively involved in dispute 
resolution activities in the Washington area as a consumer arbitrator, trained mediator, and member of the D.C. Bar Attorney Client Arbitration Board. She also serves as faculty adviser to the 
Asian Pacific American Law Students Association. Professor Izumi is chair of the AALS Section on Alternative Dispute Resolution for 1995 96.
<br>
</body>
