<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Susan Roberta Jones
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Susan Roberta Jones
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>

Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., Brandeis University<BR>
J.D., M.A., Antioch School of Law<BR>
<p>
<p>

Before joining the Law School faculty in 1988, Professor Jones was a private civil and administrative law practitioner. She 
is the supervising attorney of the Small Business Clinic. Professor Jones has held teaching positions at City University of New York, Queens College, Law School where she taught lawyering skills and clinical simulations; American University Washington College of Law, where she taught legal writing; and Antioch School of Law, where she taught in an immigration law clinic. She is also interested in the legal aspects of the arts.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
