<title>
Faculty Directory
Ira C. Lupu
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_lupu.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>


<h3>
Ira C. Lupu
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>
Louis Harkey Mayo Research Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Cornell University;<BR> 
J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Lupu joined the Law School faculty in 1990, after a sixteen-year 
teaching career at Boston University. 
After law school, where he was Case Editor of the Harvard Law Review, Professor Lupu practiced for several years at the Boston law firm of Hill & Barlow. In 1973, he joined the Boston University law faculty where he taught administrative law, constitutional law, 
family law, and legal process. He has been a visiting professor at the Univ-
ersity of California, Berkeley and at Northeastern University. In 1989 90, 
he served as Professor-in-Residence 
on the Appellate Staff of the U.S. Depart-ment of Justice, where he represented the government in a variety of cases in the Courts of Appeals. His writings are primarily in the field of constitutional law, with a recent emphasis on the religion clauses of the First Amendment.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
