<title>
Faculty Directory
Jennifer P. Lyman
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_lyman.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
Jennifer P. Lyman
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., Yale University<BR>
J.D., Stanford University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Lyman joined the Law School faculty in 1993, leaving the American University where she was director of 
the Appellate Advocacy Clinic for three years and taught an advanced evidence 
seminar. She spent 12 years at the D.C. Public Defender Service, where she was 
a staff attorney in the trial and appellate divisions, the deputy chief of the appellate division, and finally the training director. Before that, she served in the Chief Counsel s office at the Food and Drug Administration. She is on the 
faculties of training programs for trial 
and appellate lawyers, both here and abroad, emphasizing interactive teaching methods. She directs the Law School s Federal, Criminal, and Appellate Clinic, with additional interests in evidence 
and professional responsibility. 
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
