<title>
Faculty Directory
Gregory E. Maggs
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_maggsg.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=141>



<h3>
Gregory E. Maggs
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Maggs joined the Law School faculty in 1993 after teaching for two years at the University of Texas. He has clerked for Supreme Court Justices Clarence Thomas and Anthony M. Kennedy, and for Judge Joseph T. Sneed of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 
Ninth Circuit. He also worked with 
Judge Robert H. Bork at the American Enterprise Institute in Washington, D.C. His teaching interests include bankruptcy, commercial paper, contracts, insurance law, and sales. Professor Maggs is 
an officer in the U.S. Army Reserve.
<br>
</body>
</html>
