<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Joan S. Meier
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_meier.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=149>



<h3>
Joan S. Meier
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., Harvard University<BR> 
J.D., University of Chicago<BR>
<p>
<p>


Before joining the Law School in 1991, Professor Meier practiced for four years with the law firm of Winthrop, Stimson, Putnam & Roberts, doing general litigation, environmental law, and extensive pro bono work. During this time, she 
also taught clinical law at Georgetown University Law Center and family law 
at American University. Previously, as a recipient of the Georgetown Women s Law and Public Policy Fellowship, 
she taught and supervised students in women s rights litigation at Georgetown University Law Center.  As a recipient 
of the Public Interest Law Internship 
she worked for the Legal Assistance Foundation of Chicago.  In 1986 87 
she litigated freedom of information cases as a staff attorney at Public Citizen Litigation Group. In 1985, she clerked 
for the Honorable Frank H. Easterbrook of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit. Throughout her career, Professor Meier has been active in the fields of domestic violence litigation and system reform advocacy. Since coming 
to Washington, she has worked with the 
D.C. Coalition Against Domestic Viol-ence, the D.C. Superior Court Domestic Violence Coordinating Council, and, more recently, the National Task Force 
on Women, Welfare and Abuse. Professor Meier s research and publications focus primarily on the intersection of family law with criminal law and procedure. At the Law School, Professor Meier directs the Domestic Violence Clinic and also occasionally teaches family law. 
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
