<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Peter H. Meyers
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_meyers.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=149>



<h3>
Peter H. Meyers
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Adjunct Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Marietta College<BR>
J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Before joining the Law School faculty to direct the Vaccine Injury Clinic in 1994, Professor Meyers was in private practice, focusing on complex criminal and 
appellate cases, for more than 20 years.  He argued many cases before appellate courts around the country, including a case before the U.S. Supreme Court that established important standing principles. Professor Meyers was director of 
the Law School s Federal and Appellate Clinic in 1992 93.  He has also taught an advanced seminar on drugs and the 
law with Associate Dean Eric Sirulnik since 1982.  Professor Meyers has authored articles on the constitutional-
ity of drug testing, and has authored 
and edited several legal manuals for criminal defense attorneys.  He has also coordinated and made presentations 
at numerous legal education seminars around the country.  He served as director of the Center for the Study of Drug Policy, and has provided pro bono assistance to many public interest groups.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
