<title>
Faculty Directory
Terry Elaine Miller
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Terry Elaine Miller
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Adjunct Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.S., Cornell University<BR> M.A., Columbia University<BR>J.D., American University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Miller joined the Law School s Government Contracts Program Conf-erence and Research Center in 1992 
and was deputy director of that program.  In 1993 she became a visiting member 
of the faculty in the Law School s Government Procurement Law Program.  Previously, she practiced in the government contracts practice group of the 
litigation department of Fried, Frank, Harris, Shriver & Jacobson in Washington, D.C.  Following law school, she clerked for Judge Julia Cooper Mack of the D.C. Court of Appeals.  Professor Miller currently serves as executive adviser to the IRS Tax Modernization Institute and is engaged in independent consulting in the field of government contracts law.  She has taught extensively in both law school and continuing education settings 
for government contractors, federal agencies, and international entities including the United Nations and The World Bank.
<br>
</body>
</html>
