<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Thomas D. Morgan
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_morgan.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=144>



<h3>
Thomas D. Morgan
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Oppenheim Professor of Antitrust 
and Trade Regulation Law<BR>
B.A., Northwestern University<BR>
J.D., University of Chicago<BR>
<p>
<p>


Formerly dean of the Law School at Emory University, Professor Morgan teaches antitrust law, professional 
responsibility, and economic regulation of business. He is the author of widely used casebooks in all three of these 
subjects and he has written extensively in the areas of administrative law, 
government ethics, and legal education. A lecturer and consultant to law firms 
on questions of professional ethics 
and lawyer malpractice, Professor Morgan was reporter to the American 
Bar Association Commission on Professionalism. He is one of three 
professors selected by the American Law Institute to prepare its new Restatement of the Law: The Law Governing Lawyers. He has been a faculty member at the University of Illinois, a visiting professor at Cornell, and a visiting fellow at Oxford. In 1990, Professor Morgan was selected 
to serve a term as president of the Association of American Law Schools.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
