<html>
<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
William H. Painter
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_painte.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
William H. Painter
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Theodore Rinehart Professor of
Business Law<BR>
B.A., Princeton University<BR>
J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Before joining the Law School faculty, Professor Painter was Albert E. Jenner, 
Jr., Professor of Law at the University of Illinois College of Law, where he taught for fifteen years. He had served earlier as director and special counsel to the U.S. House of Representatives, Committee on Interstate and Foreign Commerce, Study of the Securities Industry. He has served on the law faculties of the University 
of Missouri, University of Michigan, and Villanova University. Prior to entering teaching, he was associated with the firm of Debevoise, Plimpton & McLean (now Debevoise & Plimpton) in New York City. His teaching interests include federal securities regulation, business planning, takeovers and tender offers, and federal income taxation of corporations. He 
has published extensively, primarily in 
the fields of corporate and securities 
law; his books include Painter on Close Corporations (3d ed., 1991), Problems and Materials in Business Planning (3d ed., 1994), The Federal Securities Code and Corporate Disclosure (1979), and Federal Regulation of Insider Trading (1968).
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT09-B35-220</DOCNO>
