<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Robert J. Peroni
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_peroni.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=144>



Robert J. Peroni
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR> Robert Kramer Research Professor of Law<BR>
B.S.C., DePaul University<BR>
J.D. Northwest-ern University<BR> LL.M., New York University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Peroni practiced law in Chicago and San Francisco and was a tenured member of the Tulane law faculty before joining the Law School faculty in 1989. He was the first recipient of Tulane s Felix Frankfurter Distinguished Teaching Award. During the 1985 86 
academic year, Professor Peroni served as a professor-in-residence in the Office of Chief Counsel of the IRS in Washington, D.C. He also has taught as a visiting 
professor on the law faculties of New York University, the University of Texas, and UCLA. Professor Peroni s research and teaching interests are in the areas 
of federal taxation, law and economics, international trade, and professional responsibility and legal ethics. He has 
co-authored four books, including the three-volume treatise U.S. International Taxation, and has also written numerous articles. Professor Peroni has taught 
a number of courses in the NYU/IRS Continuing Professional Education 
program, and, since 1991, has been 
co-chair of an annual institute on
current issues in international taxation (co-sponsored by GW and the IRS). Professor Peroni was a recipient of 
the Law School s Distinguished Faculty Service Award, selected by vote of the 1991 and 1993 graduating classes.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
