<title>
Faculty Directory
Todd David Peterson
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_peters.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=143>



<h3>
Todd David Peterson
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Brown University<BR> 
J.D., University of Michigan<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Peterson joined the Law 
School faculty in 1987. Earlier he had been a partner at the Washington, D.C., firm of Ross, Dixon & Masback, where 
he specialized in commercial litigation. Professor Peterson also served in the Department of Justice s Office of Legal Counsel, which is responsible for 
providing advice to the Attorney General and White House on constitutional law issues. He began practice in the fields of administrative and commercial litigation at the D.C. firm of Crowell & Moring.  Professor Peterson has served as a 
consultant to the National Commission on Judicial Discipline and Removal and as co-chair of the D.C. Circuit Special Committee on Race and Ethnic Bias. Professor Peterson teaches civil procedure, federal courts, and a constitutional law seminar. He writes principally in the areas of separation of powers and the federal judicial system.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
