<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Maximilian A. Pock
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_pock.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
Maximilian A. Pock
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>
J.D., University of Iowa<BR> 
S.J.D., University of Michigan<BR>
<p>
<p>



After getting his first law degree, Professor Pock joined a team of law instructors and legislative analysts at 
the University of Michigan to attempt solutions to the problems of urban 
areas. This exercise produced his first 
two monographs, Independent Special Districts: A Solution to the Metropolitan Area Problems and Consolidating Police Functions in Metropolitan Areas. After earning his S.J.D., he joined the law faculty of Emory University. In 1965 he joined the faculty of the Law School. He has published in the fields of municipal law, comparative law, legal philosophy, and insurance. He teaches contracts, equity, insurance, and conflicts. His outside activities include service as a trustee for the National Center for Auto Safety and as counsel to the American Academy of Dermatology on workers  compensation law and occupational skin diseases.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
