<title>
Faculty Directory

</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_r-hans.gif">



<h3>
Peter Raven-Hansen
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Dean for Academic Affairs; Professor of Law; Glen Earl Weston Research Professor of Law
<BR>B.A., J.D., Harvard University
<p>
<p>

Before joining the Law School faculty 
in 1980, Dean Raven-Hansen was in 
private practice with the firm of Hogan 
& Hartson in Washington, D.C., and worked as a senior economic analyst with Abt Associates, Inc., in Cambridge, Massachusetts. He now teaches civil 
procedure and a variety of public law courses, including administrative law, 
legislation, local government law, national security law, and the law of the presidency. Dean Raven-Hansen is the co-author of Understanding Civil Procedure, First Use of Nuclear Weapons, and National Security Law and the Power of the Purse, and he currently writes primarily in 
the field of national security law.  He 
is serving in the position of associate dean for academic affairs for  the 
1996 97 academic year.

<br>
</body>
