<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory

</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_robins.gif">



<h3>Alfreda Robinson
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate  Dean for Student Affairs 
and Graduate Studies and Professorial Lecturer in Law<BR>
B.A., M.A., University of Chicago; 
J.D., George Washington University
<p>
<p>


Prior to joining the Law School administration in 1989, Dean Robinson was in private practice and also served as a 
trial and appellate attorney for the U.S. Department of Justice, Civil Division. She was in charge of significant and complex litigation at the trial and appellate levels involving commercial activities, such as bankruptcy proceedings, contract suits, tort actions, employment disputes, official misconduct, foreclosures, and railroad litigation. During her tenure at Justice, she received numerous awards for outstanding performance, as well as the Attorney General Special Commendation for Outstanding Service in the Civil Division, and the TARTAR Excellence Award for Outstanding Performance from the U.S. Navy Department. As dean of students, she is academic adviser to J.D. and 
graduate law students, serves as administration liaison to student organizations, and oversees the first-year orientation and the spring academic advising 
programs. She also coordinates services to disabled students, and serves on the University Minority Faculty Recruitment Committee and the Law School Student Recruitment Committee. Her volunteer activities include acting as general 
counsel to the Greater Mt. Calvary Holy Church in the District of Columbia.
<br>
</body>
</html>
