<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Catherine J. Ross
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Catherine J. Ross
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Ph.D., J.D., Yale University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Ross joined the Law School faculty in 1996 after two years as a 
visiting professor at Boston College 
Law School.  She was a litigator for 
seven years at Paul, Weiss, Rifkind, Wharton & Garrison in New York City, and her practice included general corporate 
litigation, intellectual property and 
communications law, and public interest matters including impact litigation 
on behalf of the homeless.  In 1993 
she served as vice chair of the American Bar Association s Workshop Group on 
the Unmet Needs of Children, and was principal author of its report,  America s Children at Risk: An Agenda for Legal Action.   Since 1994 she has served as Chair of the ABA s Steering Committee 
on the Unmet Legal Needs of Children.  She serves on the editorial board of the Family Law Quarterly.  Prior to attending law school, she earned a Ph.D. in history.  She was a post-doctoral fellow at the Yale Bush Center in Child Development 
and Social Policy, and then an Assistant Professor at the Child Study Center of 
the Yale School of Medicine.  Professor Ross has taught courses on children 
and family, poverty, and evidence.
<br>
</body>
</html>
