<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Joan E. Schaffner
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Joan E. Schaffner
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law<BR>
B.S., J.D., University of Southern California<BR> M.S., Massachusetts Institute of Technology<BR>
<p>
<p>



Prior to joining the Law School faculty 
in 1992, Professor Schaffner practiced as a litigation associate in the Los Angeles firm of Irell & Manella and served as 
law clerk to the Honorable Mariana R. Pfaelzer of the U.S. District Court for the Central District of California.  During that time she also served as Convenor of the Advisory Group on Federal Benefits to the Gender Bias Task Force of the Ninth Circuit.  In addition to her law degree, Professor Schaffner has a master s degree in mechanical engineering from M.I.T.  She currently teaches civil procedure and patent law and writes in these fields as well. She serves as faculty adviser to Lambda Law and is the editor-in-chief 
of the AIPLA Quarterly Journal.
<br>
</body>
