<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Teresa Moran Schwartz
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_tschwa.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
Teresa Moran Schwartz
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
J.B. and Maurice C. Shapiro Professor of Public Interest Law<BR>
B.A., Stanford University<BR> 
J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Schwartz joined the Law School faculty after serving as attorney-adviser to Federal Trade Commissioner Mary Gardiner Jones. She graduated first in her class from the Law School and was a member of the Law Review. She teaches in the areas of torts, products 
liability law, and administrative law, and she has written over 20 articles, primarily in the area of product safety and liability. In the early 1980s, while serving as 
associate dean of students, she started the Enrichment Program, a distinguished speakers series that she directed until 1993. She served as associate dean for academic affairs from 1988 to 1993. Professor Schwartz serves on the board of the YWCA of the National Capital Area and is a member of the editorial board of the Administrative Law Review and the Board of Trustees of the Food and Drug Law Institute. In 1977 78 she served as a White House Fellow. Currently on leave from the Law School, Professor Schwartz is serving as Deputy Director of the Bureau of Consumer Protection, Federal Trade Commission.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
