Faculty Directory
David E. Seidelson
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_seidel.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
David E. Seidelson
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Lyle T. Alverson Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., LL.B., University of Pittsburgh<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Seidelson was Legislation Editor of the University of Pittsburgh 
Law Review. He was also a recipient of the Blackburn Memorial Award at the University of Pittsburgh. He practiced with a Pittsburgh law firm, trying and arguing approximately two hundred cases. Since joining the Law School fac-ulty in 1960, he has written approximately sixty articles, most of them on subjects in his teaching areas of torts, evidence and conflict of laws. Professor Seidelson is a member of the Order of the Coif.
<br>
</body>
</html>
