<title>
Faculty Directory
David James Sharpe
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_sharpe.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=152>



<h3>
David James Sharpe
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>Harold Paul<BR> 
Green Research Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., University of North Carolina<BR>
LL.B., S.J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>



During and after law school, Professor Sharpe served in the Navy, in state 
government consulting, and in the Atomic Energy Commission.  He began teaching law at Boston University in 1957 and has taught at GW Law School since 1960.  He was a visiting faculty member at Tulane Law School in 1982.  He has been an editor for the casebooks Law and Medicine (1979), Medical Liability (1991), Admiralty (1974, 1986, 1996), 
and Judicial Relief (1996).  At present 
he teaches and writes in admiralty and remedies, and he is an arbitrator and consultant on maritime law topics.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
