<title>
Faculty Directory
Amy E. Sloan
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/not.gif">



<h3>
Amy E. Sloan
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Legal Research and Writing<BR> Director of the Legal Research and Writing Program<BR>
B.A., University of Texas<BR> 
J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Sloan administers and teaches in the first-year Legal Research and Writ-ing Program.  She also taught in the 
program as a member of the part-time faculty during the 1993 94 academic year.  Professor Sloan taught for two 
years at Catholic University s law school, where she was Assistant Director of the Lawyering Skills Program.  She also developed the legal research and writing curriculum for Catholic s International Law Institute summer program.  Before entering teaching, Professor Sloan clerked at the U.S. District Court for the District of Maryland for the Honorable William M. Nickerson and the Honorable Edward S. Northrop.  She is active in the Legal Writing Institute and the Association 
of Legal Writing Directors.
<br>
</body>
