<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Louis B. Sohn
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_sohn.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=143>



<h3>
Louis B. Sohn
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Distinguished Research Professor of Law<BR>Director of Research and Studies of the International Rule of Law Institute<BR>
Dipl.Sc.M., LL.M., John Casimir University (Poland)<BR> LL.M., S.J.D., Harvard University<BR>
<p>
<p>



After teaching for 35 years at Harvard Law School, 20 of them as Bemis Professor of International Law, Professor Sohn taught for ten years as Woodruff Professor of International Law at the University of Georgia School of Law.  
He took part in the San Francisco Conference that established the United Nations.  He worked from time to time 
at the United Nations and the Depart-ment of State on the settlement of international disputes, disarmament, human rights and law of the sea.  He served as Counselor on International Law in the Department of State in 1970 71, and as 
a United States delegate to the Law of the Sea Conference from 1974 to 1982.  He participated as United States Counsel in two cases before the International Court of Justice, relating to Namibia (1971) and Nicaragua (1984).  Professor Sohn was president of the American Society of International Law from 1988 
to 1990, and chairman of the Section of International Law and Practice of the American Bar Association in 1992 93.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
