<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Lewis D. Solomon
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_solomo.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=148>



<h3>
Lewis D. Solomon
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>Arthur Selwyn 
Miller Research Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Cornell University<BR>
J.D., Yale University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Prior to joining the Law School faculty 
in 1977, Professor Solomon served as 
a law clerk to a Federal district court judge in Wilmington, Delaware; practiced with a law firm in New York; and taught at the law school of the University of Missouri Kansas City. He is the author 
of numerous books and articles in the areas of corporate and securities law, 
taxation, business and estate planning, and policy-making. He has served as 
the Inaugural Arthur Young Visiting Professor of Tax Law at Monash University in Australia, the Inaugural Rupert and Lillian Radford Visiting Professor of Law at Southern Methodist University and the Frances Lewis Schol-ar-in-Residence at Washington and Lee Law School. He has also taught at the Shanghai University of Technology in China, the University of Sydney Law School, Australian National University Law School, and the University of 
Miami Law School.
<br>
</body>
</html>
