<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory

</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/NOT.GIF">



<h3>Robert V. Stanek
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Assistant Dean for Admissions and Financial Aid<BR>
B.A., Pennsylvania State University; 
J.D., George Washington University
<p>
<p>


Nine years after graduating from Penn State, Dean Stanek began his law studies at GW. In the interim he held positions in teaching, counseling, financial aid, and admissions. After his graduation from law school he accepted the position of 
assistant dean and director of admis-sions at the Law School. In 1988, he 
also assumed responsibility for the school s financial aid programs. During the 1993 94 academic year, Dean Stanek 
was on leave from the Law School and served as visiting associate executive director of Law School Admission Services in Newtown, Pennsylvania.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
