<title>
Faculty Directory
Joan H. Strand
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_strand.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=147>



<h3>
Joan H. Strand
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Clinical Law<BR>
B.A., J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Strand has taught in the field of clinical legal education for over 15 years. After graduation from law school in 1975, she supervised students working on civil cases in the D.C. Law Students in Court Program. In 1979, she joined the Law School faculty, where she directs the Civil Litigation Clinic. She is an active member of the D.C. legal community, having served in several leadership positions in the D.C. Bar, including co-chairing the Family Law Section, chairing a committee to update a comprehensive manual on local practice, and serving on the Public Service 
Activities Committee. In 1994 she was given the D.C. Bar s Best Project Award 
for chairing the D.C. Practice Manual Revision Committee. Professor Strand 
has taught continuing legal education courses to train lawyers in private 
practice how to handle pro bono cases 
in the areas of landlord-tenant law and child custody. In 1993 94, she served as Secretary of the D.C. Bar, and is currently a member of the Board of Governors.
<br>
</body>
</html>
