<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_trangs.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=147>



<h3>
Roger H. Trangsrud
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Professor of Law<BR>
B.A., Carleton College<BR> 
J.D., University of Chicago<BR>
<p>
<p>



After serving on the University of Chicago Law Review, Professor Trangsrud clerked for Justice Walter Rogosheske 
of the Minnesota Supreme Court and practiced law with the D.C. firm of Hogan & Hartson. In 1982 he joined the faculty of the Law School where he has taught civil procedure, federal jurisdiction, remedies, and complex litigation. His writings are primarily in the fields of complex 
litigation and jurisdiction. In 1990 Profes-sor Trangsrud took leave from the Law School to practice with the law firm of Ross, Dixon & Masback in D.C. For several years he has served as a pro bono mediator in the D.C. Circuit Appellate Mediation Program. In 1993 he was appointed the associate dean for academic affairs; he 
is on leave from his administrative duties during the 1996 97 academic year.
<br>
</body>
