<h3>
Robert Tuttle
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Law
B.A., College of William and Mary<BR>M.A., Lutheran School of Theology at Chicago<BR>J.D., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>



Professor Tuttle joined the faculty in 1994. Since graduating from the Law School in 1991, he has been pursuing a Ph.D. in religious ethics at the University of Virginia, and he previously taught as an associate professional lecturer at the Law School. Professor Tuttle teaches in the areas of property, trusts and estates, jurisprudence, and professional responsibility. His research and writing interests include legal ethics, law and religion,
and moral philosophy.
<br>
