<head>
<title>
GWLAW Spring '97 Registration for 1L's
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>
<h5>GW Law School<br>
Records Office</h5><br><P>
<h4>Spring '97 Registration Information for First Year Students <br>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h4>


<ul>

<li>You will be registered by the Records Office in the middle of November. A statement will be
mailed to your current address (please check GWizard to make sure that it is
correct).<br></li><br>

<li>Full-time Day students (SECTIONS 11, 12, 13, 14) will be registered for the following
courses within their current sections:
     <dd>203 - Contracts II (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>208 - Property (4 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>213 - Civil Procedure II (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>214 - Constitutional Law I (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>217 - Introduction to Advocacy (2 credit hours)<i>--- Note: Same section as Fall
'96 Legal Research and Writing)</i>
<br></li><br>
<li>Full-time Day/Evening students (SECTION 15) will be registered for the following courses
and sections (section 20 being evening classes and section 15 day):
     <dd>203-20 - Contracts II (2 credit hours)  <br>
     <dd>210-20 - Criminal Law (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>213-15 - Civil Procedure II (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>214-20 - Constitutional Law I (3 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>217 - Introduction to Advocacy (2 credit hours) <i>--- Note: Same section as Fall '96
Legal Research and Writing)</i><br>
     <dd>218-15 - Professional Responsibility (2 credit hours)<br>
</li><br>
<li>Part-time Evening students (SECTION 20) will be registered for the following evening
classes:
     <dd>203-20 - Contracts II (2 credit hours) <br>
     <dd>210-20 - Criminal Law (3 credit hours)<br>
     <dd>214-20 - Constitutional Law I (3 credit hours)<br>
     <dd>217 - Introduction to Advocacy (2 credit hours) <i>--- Note: Same section as Fall '96
Legal Research and Writing)</i><br>
</li><br>

<li>Classrooms will be posted on the first day of classes (January 8th).  First day assignments will
be posted behind the glass cases on the 1st floor of Stockton Hall (across from the student
lounge) as soon as they are received by the Records Office.  First day assignments will NOT be
posted online.</li>

<br><br>
<li><B>PLEASE BE ADVISED THAT IF STUDENT ACCOUNTS, STUDENT HEALTH,
UNIVERSITY PARKING OR ANY OTHER UNIVERSITY OFFICE PLACES A HOLD ON
YOUR RECORD (DUE TO OUTSTANDING BALANCE OR FAILURE TO PROVIDE
PROOF OF IMMUNIZATION, FOR EXAMPLE), WE WILL BE UNABLE TO REGISTER
YOU FOR THE SPRING SEMESTER.</B></li>
<br><br>
<li><B>PLEASE CHECK YOUR RECORD ON GWIZARD (UNDER "DISPLAY HOLDS" -
IN THE STUDENT INFO MENU) FOR ANY HOLDS. YOUR RECORD MUST BE
CLEARED BY NOVEMBER 8TH OR WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO REGISTER YOU FOR
THE SPRING SEMESTER.</B></li><br><br>
</ul>


<p><br>
<h5><i>Updated: 10/28/96</i><br>

<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h5>

