<head>
<title>
GWLaw Spring '97 Registration Dates
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>
<h5>GW Law School<br>
Records Office</h5><br><P>
<h4>Important Dates for Spring '97 Registration<br>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h4>


<H5><I>(Exerpt from The Evening Exchange Newsletter, by Frank Durand, Asst. Dean of
Student Affairs)</I></H5>
<ul>
   <li><B>Monday, October 28, 1996 --- <i>Registration packets available</i></B>
      <dd>Registration packets, which contain all of the materials you will need to prepare for
registration, will be distributed to all <B>second-,third-, fourth-year and LL.M. students</B> via
their mail slots.  If for any reason you do not receive a packet, please check with the Records
Office.<br>
     <dd><B>Attention first-year students:</B> a packet for first-year students will also be
available on October 28th.  This packet contains useful information about your course schedule
for Spring 1997.  Please note that <B>first-year students do not register for Spring 1997
courses;</B> registration of all first-year students will be done automatically by the Records
Office.<br>
<dd><br>
  </li>

    <li><B>Thursday, October 31, 1996 --- <i>Registration for 3L's, 4L's, and LLM
students</i></B>
      <dd>All third- and fourth-year students and LL.M. students register today, between 3pm
and 8pm in room LL101.  At the time you submit your registration form, you will complete and
submit a form designating your PASS class selection. If you are not familiar with the PASS
system, please click <a href="/rec/sp97pass.htm">here</a>.
      <dd><b>Registration is done by lottery -- it is NOT conducted on a first-come, first-served
basis.</b>
     <dd>If classes oversubscribe due to enrollment caps or room size, students are bumped <i>by
lottery</i>.
     <dd>Students who are bumped from a class may add another class the following day, during
winter break, or once Spring classes begin.
     <dd>Evening students are given priority for seats in evening courses.
     <dd>No student will be allowed to register for more than <i>15 credits</i> at the initial
registration; students will be allowed to add courses beyond 15 credits in January.
     <dd><b>Students my NOT register for a wait-listed class unless they win a seat through the
lottery.  At registration, students interested in a wait-listed class must instead sign their names to
the wait list.</b><br>
<dd><br>
   </li>

   <li><B>Wednesday, November 6, 1996 --- <i>Lottery results and any bump lists
posted</i></B>
     <dd>Results of lotteries for wait listed classes, as well as bump lists from any oversubscribed
classes following the registration of 3L's, 4L's, and LLM's, will be posted on the bulletin board
outside the Records Office.  They will also be posted online here on the Records Office
Homepage.<br>
<dd><br>
   </li>
    <li><B>Thursday, November 7, 1996 --- <i>Registration for 2L's</i></B>
       <dd>All second year students register today between 3pm and 8pm in room LL101.  At the
time you submit your registration form, you will complete and submit a form designating your
PASS class selection. If you are not familiar with the PASS system, please click <a
href="/rec/sp97pass.htm">here</a>.
     <dd>Second year evening students must enter Civil Procedure II, Section 20 (3 credit hours),
as well as elective courses, one of which should be designated as your PASS class, to fill out your
schedule to 8-10 credit hours. <b>Evening students should NOT use Civil Procedure II as the
PASS class,</b> since it is part of your foundation 1L/2L curriculum, your seat in this class is
already assured when you register.
      <dd><b>Registration is done by lottery -- it is NOT conducted on a first-come, first-served
basis.</b>
     <dd>If classes oversubscribe due to enrollment caps or room size, students are bumped <i>by
lottery</i>.
     <dd>Students who are bumped from a class may add another class the following day, during
winter break, or once Spring classes begin.
     <dd>Evening students are given priority for seats in evening courses.
     <dd>No student will be allowed to register for more than <i>15 credits</i> at the initial
registration; students will be allowed to add courses beyond 15 credits in January.
     <dd><b>Students my NOT register for a wait-listed class unless they win a seat through the
lottery.  At registration, students interested in a wait-listed class must instead sign their names to
the wait list.</b><br>
<dd><br>
   </li>

    <li><B>Wednesday, November 13, 1996 --- <i>Lottery results and any bump lists
posted</i></B>
     <dd>Results of lotteries for wait listed classes, as well as bump lists from any oversubscribed
classes following the registration of 2L's, will be posted on the bulletin board outside the Records
Office.  They will also be posted online here on the Records Office Homepage.<br>
<dd><br>
   </li>
    <li><B>Friday, November 15, 1996</B>
       <dd>This is the final day for students to add or drop courses or make any other adjustments
to their Spring 1997 schedules until after the end of the Fall '96 final exams (December 23, 1996). 
<br>
</ul>

<p><br>
<h5><i>Updated: 10/28/96</i><br>

<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13></h5>

