<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory

Arnold W. Reitze, Jr.
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_reitze.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=150>



<h3>

Arnold W. Reitze, Jr.
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
J.B. and Maurice C. Shapiro Professor of Environmental Law<BR> Co-Director of the Environmental Law Program<BR>
B.A., Fairleigh Dickinson University<BR>
J.D., Rutgers University<BR> 
M.P.H., Johns Hopkins University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Reitze has directed the environmental law program at the Law School since 1970. During the 1960s he represented environmental groups involved in air pollution, water pollution, solid waste, and coal mining issues. In 1969 he co-authored the City of Cleveland s air pollution code. Since coming to GW in 1970 he has represented Alaskan natives on environmental issues, assisted in wetland acquisition projects, and has been a consultant to the Army Corps of Engineers, the Interstate Commission of the Poto-mac River Basin, the Environmental Protection Agency, the National Institute of Occupational Safety and Health, 
and private law firms. In 1983 84 he 
was a member of the National Acad-
emy of Sciences, Committee on De-
militarizing Chemical Munitions and Agents. Professor Reitze has authored 
or co-authored more than one hundred 
articles, research studies, and books on environmental law. His most recent book is Air Pollution Control. He is also a faculty editor of The Environmental Lawyer.
<br>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
