<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Laurent Romain Hourcle
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_hourcl.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=144>



<h3>
Laurent Romain Hourcle
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Environmental Law; Co-Director of the Environmental Law Program<BR>
B.S., Boston University; M.A., Central Michigan University; J.D., Duke University<BR>
LL.M., George Washington University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Hourcle joined the faculty in 1992 after a 21-year career in the U.S. Air Force. At the time of his retirement, he was serving as a Colonel assigned to 
the Department of Defense s Office of General Counsel, where he was responsible for environmental and occupational safety and health law and legal issues involving base closure and reuse. Prior 
to that assignment, he was the first chief of the Air Force Judge Advocate General s Environmental Law Division and served in a variety of assignments that involved environmental, public 
international, and government contracts law. His areas of interest include 
environmental responsibilities of federal agencies and the interrelationship of 
government contract and environmental law. Since joining the faculty, he has 
written and served as a consultant to 
the Departments of Energy and Defense and the Environmental Protection Agency on these issues. Professor Hourcl teaches courses on the 
control of solid and hazardous wastes, environmental issues for federal 
facilities, and environmental issues 
in government contracting.
<br>
</body>
</html>
