<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Richard J. Pierce, Jr.
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_pierce.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=142>



<h3>
Richard J. Pierce, Jr.
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Lyle T. Alverson Professor of Law<BR>
B.S., Lehigh University<BR>
J.D., University of Virginia<BR>
<p>
<p>



Before joining the Law School faculty, Professor Pierce taught at Columbia University, the University of Virginia, Southern Methodist University, Tulane University, and the University of Kansas. He also was dean of the University of Pittsburgh School of Law. He practiced with Sutherland, Asbill & Brennan in Washington, D.C. Professor Pierce is author or co-author of Administrative Law Treatise (3d vol. 1993); Admini-
strative Law and Process (1992); Economic Regulation (1994); and Regulated Industries (1992). He has 
written numerous articles on govern-ment regulation, regulatory economics, and the characteristics of the markets 
for electricity and natural gas.
<br>
</body>
</html>
