<head>
<title>
Faculty Directory
Elizabeth Glass Geltman
</title>
</head>
<font face="HELVETICA,arial" size=-1>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<br>



<img src="http://128.164.161.15/s_geltma.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=145>



<h3>
Elizabeth Glass Geltman
</h3><img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" width=357 height=17><p>
Associate Professor of Environmental Law 
B.A., Cornell University<BR>
J.D., University of Baltimore<BR>
LL.M., Georgetown University<BR>
<p>
<p>


Professor Geltman joined the Law School 
faculty in 1991.  After working for the Honorable Kenneth Starr of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the D.C. Circuit and the Honorable Paul Alpert of the Maryland Court of Special Appeals, Professor Geltman worked at the Washington, D.C., offices of Fulbright & Jaworski and Hunton & Williams.  She is currently of counsel to the Washington, D.C., office 
of Squire, Sanders & Dempsey.  She has written ten books on environmental law issues, including Environmental Issues 
in Business Volumes 1 & 2 (1994); Environmental Law and Business (1994); Corporations (1994); Contracts (1994); Environmental Audits (1995); and Securities Disclosure of Environmental Problems (1995).  She is co-author of Environmental Law and Bankruptcy.  Professor Geltman has spoken at various legal seminars and conferences and is widely published in newspapers and law reviews on issues concerning the interplay between business, real estate, environmental law, and natural resources. 
Her primary teaching and research interests include property, environmental law, environmental issues in business transactions, corporations, and securities law.
<br>
</body>
</html>
